1
00:00:38,180 --> 00:00:44,690
This film is based on historical facts blended with artistic fiction.

2
00:00:46,260 --> 00:00:48,450
The ever-unchanging traitor

3
00:00:48,460 --> 00:00:52,700
is Suyang who now sits upon the dragon throne!

4
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:57,990
In 1452, Yi Hong-wi ascended the throne at the age of twelve.

5
00:00:57,990 --> 00:01:06,560
The following year, his uncle, Grand Prince Suyang, rebelled, seized the throne, and proclaimed himself king.

6
00:01:06,560 --> 00:01:07,990
The treacherous minister Han Myong-hoe,

7
00:01:08,260 --> 00:01:12,960
who deceived His Majesty and threw the realm
into chaos, shall surely face the wrath of heaven.

8
00:01:15,900 --> 00:01:17,580
Han Myong-hoe!

9
00:01:17,860 --> 00:01:21,950
Your treasonous conspiracy and
usurpation of His Majesty's throne

10
00:01:22,310 --> 00:01:25,090
shall not escape the wrath of heaven.

11
00:01:35,330 --> 00:01:36,490
Your Majesty.

12
00:01:42,570 --> 00:01:44,300
Please eat.

13
00:01:46,940 --> 00:01:50,250
Take the table away.

14
00:01:53,970 --> 00:01:55,210
Your Majesty.

15
00:01:56,480 --> 00:01:57,870
You must eat.

16
00:01:58,090 --> 00:01:59,480
I said take it away.

17
00:01:59,740 --> 00:02:01,290
You must eat, Your Majesty.

18
00:02:01,300 --> 00:02:02,890
I said take it away!

19
00:02:03,770 --> 00:02:05,290
Your Majesty,

20
00:02:05,810 --> 00:02:08,110
the Royal Secretary, Han Myong-hoe,
requests an audience.

21
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:11,390
Your Majesty,

22
00:02:12,020 --> 00:02:14,040
your servant Han Myong-hoe seeks an audience.

23
00:02:23,850 --> 00:02:26,630
Come in.

24
00:02:40,490 --> 00:02:42,580
I hear this is your second day of refusing food.

25
00:02:43,420 --> 00:02:46,550
Why do you reject your meals?

26
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:53,010
Is it my turn now?

27
00:02:54,370 --> 00:02:56,320
What do you mean, Your Majesty?

28
00:02:57,920 --> 00:02:58,830
I mean,

29
00:03:01,540 --> 00:03:04,710
is it my turn to scream like they did?

30
00:03:11,060 --> 00:03:14,800
Those men were great traitors
who plotted rebellion behind your back.

31
00:03:16,460 --> 00:03:19,350
They deserved to scream.

32
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:22,960
Your Majesty, you are guilty of nothing.

33
00:03:23,950 --> 00:03:26,690
Why should you scream?

34
00:03:29,170 --> 00:03:32,320
You knew nothing of their treasonous scheme,

35
00:03:33,250 --> 00:03:34,770
and even if you had,

36
00:03:36,030 --> 00:03:37,950
you would never have allowed it.

37
00:03:39,420 --> 00:03:41,230
Isn't that so?

38
00:03:43,540 --> 00:03:44,450
Or

39
00:03:46,710 --> 00:03:48,290
was it otherwise?

40
00:03:50,940 --> 00:03:51,490
What

41
00:03:58,290 --> 00:03:59,650
should I do?

42
00:04:33,070 --> 00:04:33,790
Now!

43
00:04:45,330 --> 00:04:45,940
Shoot!

44
00:04:46,830 --> 00:04:50,380
Will you shut up? Be quiet!

45
00:04:50,390 --> 00:04:51,880
Catch it!

46
00:04:52,760 --> 00:04:54,190
Now you won't even get a scrap of meat.

47
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:54,980
Which way did it go?

48
00:04:54,980 --> 00:04:56,680
Why do you always start fighting
the moment you meet?

49
00:04:58,850 --> 00:04:59,520
Spread out.

50
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:00,630
Spread out.

51
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:06,130
Damn it.

52
00:05:08,990 --> 00:05:10,110
I told you to breathe quietly,

53
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,560
but you just ignore me.

54
00:05:12,630 --> 00:05:15,440
No respect for your village chief at all.

55
00:05:19,380 --> 00:05:21,460
Chief!

56
00:05:22,100 --> 00:05:23,990
Where are you?

57
00:05:24,420 --> 00:05:26,390
Chief!

58
00:05:27,210 --> 00:05:28,170
Where are you?

59
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:31,410
What's that fool going on about now?

60
00:05:51,190 --> 00:05:52,250
No way.

61
00:06:12,050 --> 00:06:13,570
Help!

62
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:35,100
What are you doing lying there?

63
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:37,130
Want to take a nap?

64
00:06:37,320 --> 00:06:38,440
Honestly,

65
00:06:38,450 --> 00:06:41,480
everyone's running around
trying to catch a roe deer,

66
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:43,570
and look at him, fast asleep.

67
00:06:43,580 --> 00:06:45,150
Oh dear, oh dear.

68
00:06:45,980 --> 00:06:47,010
Yeah,

69
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:50,120
he's been a heavy sleeper
since he was little. Let's go.

70
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:54,830
A tiger! There's a tiger!

71
00:06:54,840 --> 00:06:56,210
Father, go on and rest.

72
00:06:56,220 --> 00:06:57,950
Sleeping in the middle
of a deep mountain. Oh dear.

73
00:06:57,960 --> 00:06:58,910
Help!

74
00:06:59,420 --> 00:07:00,750
You brat!

75
00:07:00,850 --> 00:07:02,460
I...

76
00:07:23,380 --> 00:07:24,390
Sir!

77
00:07:26,890 --> 00:07:27,570
Sir!

78
00:07:30,130 --> 00:07:31,660
What's this place?

79
00:07:38,050 --> 00:07:39,140
Is that real?

80
00:07:42,190 --> 00:07:43,230
Is that white rice?

81
00:07:51,400 --> 00:07:52,920
Looks like I really am dead.

82
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:55,040
I've made it to paradise.

83
00:07:57,450 --> 00:07:58,050
This one

84
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:00,450
is real!

85
00:08:04,060 --> 00:08:06,740
He's awake! He's awake!

86
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:10,390
You collapsed in a valley.

87
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:11,470
Lucky to be alive.

88
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:13,210
Yes, yes.

89
00:08:17,990 --> 00:08:20,460
But you're a stranger.

90
00:08:20,710 --> 00:08:21,510
Where are you from?

91
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:24,760
I'm from Gwangcheon Valley.

92
00:08:24,770 --> 00:08:25,520
Gwangcheon Valley?

93
00:08:25,780 --> 00:08:26,520
Gwangcheon Valley?

94
00:08:26,710 --> 00:08:28,450
What village is this?

95
00:08:28,470 --> 00:08:29,390
This is Norugol Valley.

96
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:31,080
Ah, Norugol Valley.

97
00:08:31,300 --> 00:08:32,320
How did you end up here?

98
00:08:32,330 --> 00:08:36,120
I wanted to catch some roe deer, so...

99
00:08:36,130 --> 00:08:38,790
Catch roe deer?

100
00:08:39,210 --> 00:08:39,680
Yes.

101
00:08:40,030 --> 00:08:41,370
Why would you catch roe deer?

102
00:08:41,380 --> 00:08:43,420
To eat, of course.

103
00:08:43,430 --> 00:08:44,750
You eat roe deer?

104
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:45,400
Yes.

105
00:08:45,410 --> 00:08:50,370
Roe deer meat is so gamey. You eat that?

106
00:08:51,690 --> 00:08:53,790
People only ate that in the old days.

107
00:08:54,250 --> 00:08:56,780
We have no meat. We're starving.

108
00:08:57,490 --> 00:08:59,940
Hey, is there some big celebration in the village?

109
00:08:59,950 --> 00:09:01,690
Such a big feast.

110
00:09:01,690 --> 00:09:04,220
Today is my son's birthday.

111
00:09:04,870 --> 00:09:06,000
You throw such a big feast

112
00:09:06,020 --> 00:09:06,900
just for a child's birthday?

113
00:09:06,900 --> 00:09:07,820
Just some simple food.

114
00:09:07,820 --> 00:09:09,170
Who is this kid?

115
00:09:09,190 --> 00:09:10,600
Such a big celebration for his birthday.

116
00:09:11,050 --> 00:09:13,440
It's a happy day. Have a drink with us.

117
00:09:13,710 --> 00:09:15,020
Eat some meat too.

118
00:09:15,090 --> 00:09:15,860
Oh my.

119
00:09:16,130 --> 00:09:18,210
Oh my, can I really eat this?

120
00:09:18,810 --> 00:09:19,510
This isn't roe deer meat.

121
00:09:20,370 --> 00:09:20,710
Good.

122
00:09:21,620 --> 00:09:23,090
Oh my, grabbing it with bare hands.

123
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:26,140
I'm really starving.

124
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:31,230
In our village,

125
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:33,210
we don't even have a bite to eat.
We're dying of hunger.

126
00:09:33,220 --> 00:09:36,310
How can your village eat so well?

127
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:40,330
You look like an uneducated country bumpkin,

128
00:09:40,640 --> 00:09:42,030
so I'll let you in on a secret.

129
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:48,760
One day, an old man with
a long beard came to our village.

130
00:09:55,610 --> 00:09:57,330
He used to be a Minister of Justice.

131
00:09:57,590 --> 00:09:58,790
Good day, my lord.

132
00:09:59,810 --> 00:10:02,240
The Yangban Lord from Hanyang

133
00:10:02,630 --> 00:10:06,860
was exiled to this deep mountain forest.

134
00:10:07,740 --> 00:10:09,580
We had to give him a house to live in,

135
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:13,040
Bring me something to drink and eat.

136
00:10:13,050 --> 00:10:16,580
tighten our belts to prepare his meals.

137
00:10:20,850 --> 00:10:22,360
Catch that for me.

138
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:23,770
That chicken.

139
00:10:23,780 --> 00:10:25,150
And on top of that, that damned Yangban

140
00:10:25,160 --> 00:10:27,180
acted like a real high official,

141
00:10:27,190 --> 00:10:29,630
treating villagers like servants.

142
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:33,080
But one day,

143
00:10:33,340 --> 00:10:35,840
he started bringing in wealth.

144
00:10:36,460 --> 00:10:36,970
How did the wealth come?

145
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:38,290
By donkeys.

146
00:10:38,710 --> 00:10:39,670
Donkeys?

147
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:40,490
Yes.

148
00:10:40,830 --> 00:10:41,550
Donkeys.

149
00:10:44,730 --> 00:10:46,620
Donkeys loaded with full packsaddles

150
00:10:46,630 --> 00:10:48,720
lined up to Norugol Valley.

151
00:10:53,810 --> 00:10:56,790
Meat, rice, cloth, fine silk.

152
00:10:57,270 --> 00:10:59,510
Those Yangban Lords in Hanyang
have sharp instincts.

153
00:10:59,510 --> 00:11:01,670
They guessed that this exiled Minister of Justice

154
00:11:01,680 --> 00:11:03,830
would soon return to his post.

155
00:11:05,270 --> 00:11:06,560
But the minister grew bored

156
00:11:06,570 --> 00:11:08,960
and began teaching the village children to read.

157
00:11:10,280 --> 00:11:10,870
Before long,

158
00:11:11,160 --> 00:11:12,800
the illiterate country kids

159
00:11:12,810 --> 00:11:14,610
memorized the Thousand Character Classic

160
00:11:14,620 --> 00:11:17,800
and mastered the teachings of Confucius,

161
00:11:17,810 --> 00:11:19,170
Mencius, and the sages

162
00:11:20,510 --> 00:11:23,630
Just as those Yangban Lords
expected, not long after,

163
00:11:23,640 --> 00:11:26,630
the minister's exile ended
and he went back to Hanyang.

164
00:11:27,130 --> 00:11:29,390
He took a few bright children to
study further in the capital,

165
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:32,510
and one of them even passed
the highest civil service exam.

166
00:11:49,140 --> 00:11:49,980
In short,

167
00:11:49,990 --> 00:11:52,510
Norugol Valley struck gold.

168
00:11:52,520 --> 00:11:56,290
We made it!

169
00:11:56,780 --> 00:11:57,920
-Gold? -Gold?

170
00:11:57,930 --> 00:11:58,680
That's right.

171
00:11:59,290 --> 00:12:00,490
That could

172
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:03,810
happen here in Gwangcheon Valley too!

173
00:12:04,850 --> 00:12:05,630
How?

174
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:09,700
Not long ago, things changed in Hanyang.

175
00:12:09,710 --> 00:12:12,040
The old king was deposed,
and a new king was put on the throne, right?

176
00:12:12,330 --> 00:12:14,130
That means there will be plenty of

177
00:12:14,140 --> 00:12:15,570
Yangban Lords sent into exile.

178
00:12:15,580 --> 00:12:16,710
I hear one of them

179
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:20,350
is being sent right here to Yeongwol.

180
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:22,070
Don't spread this around yet.

181
00:12:22,480 --> 00:12:23,200
Who is it?

182
00:12:23,230 --> 00:12:25,840
Anyway, he must be
an extremely high-ranking official.

183
00:12:25,850 --> 00:12:27,630
A magnificent man

184
00:12:27,640 --> 00:12:31,700
with a thick, long beard.

185
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:33,000
What good does that do?

186
00:12:33,010 --> 00:12:34,920
He'll just go to Norugol Valley.

187
00:12:34,930 --> 00:12:35,680
No.

188
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:37,620
We must bring him to

189
00:12:37,630 --> 00:12:40,020
our Gwangcheon Valley by any means necessary.

190
00:12:40,610 --> 00:12:43,290
If we serve that Yangban Lord well,

191
00:12:43,690 --> 00:12:45,810
then other Yangban Lords will

192
00:12:45,820 --> 00:12:47,470
come flocking to us like
strings of yellow croaker fish.

193
00:12:47,590 --> 00:12:50,040
Yellow croaker must taste good.

194
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:51,440
No!

195
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:55,120
Do you think those exiled Yangbans

196
00:12:55,130 --> 00:12:57,060
will ever repent and see the light?

197
00:12:57,200 --> 00:13:00,740
Oh please! They spend their days
drinking and harassing women.

198
00:13:00,750 --> 00:13:02,910
The slightest thing goes wrong,

199
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:05,860
they run to the county office
and get the villagers beaten.

200
00:13:05,870 --> 00:13:06,660
Exactly.

201
00:13:06,670 --> 00:13:08,340
With those exiled Yangbans,

202
00:13:08,350 --> 00:13:10,920
we have to give up our houses,
cook for them, serve them,

203
00:13:10,930 --> 00:13:13,460
and watch them every day to
keep them from running away.

204
00:13:13,470 --> 00:13:15,170
If anything goes wrong with him,

205
00:13:15,190 --> 00:13:17,510
our whole village will go up in flames,

206
00:13:17,510 --> 00:13:19,860
just like this tree.

207
00:13:20,320 --> 00:13:22,090
Hey, keep your voice down.

208
00:13:22,730 --> 00:13:25,550
Look at you, so poor.

209
00:13:26,040 --> 00:13:27,450
Those slouching little brats,

210
00:13:27,460 --> 00:13:28,770
what do you feed them?

211
00:13:29,030 --> 00:13:30,300
When they're hungry with nothing to eat,

212
00:13:30,310 --> 00:13:31,760
you just smack them a few times,
give them water,

213
00:13:31,770 --> 00:13:33,020
and send them to sleep.

214
00:13:33,620 --> 00:13:35,290
But in Norugol Valley?

215
00:13:35,290 --> 00:13:36,890
Just because a little kid had a birthday,

216
00:13:36,910 --> 00:13:39,650
they had meat soup and white rice.

217
00:13:39,660 --> 00:13:42,470
The whole village ate together
till their bellies were round.

218
00:13:42,480 --> 00:13:44,890
Chicken, pork, everything you could want.

219
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:47,940
And it was just a child's birthday!

220
00:13:52,260 --> 00:13:53,520
That white rice,

221
00:13:54,090 --> 00:13:58,120
it was steaming hot, damn it!

222
00:13:58,980 --> 00:14:00,070
The grains were separate,

223
00:14:00,080 --> 00:14:02,750
white and fragrant.

224
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:05,600
I truly thought I'd reached paradise.

225
00:14:05,870 --> 00:14:09,890
Seriously, when was
the last time we had white rice?

226
00:14:10,460 --> 00:14:12,120
-Remember? -Probably

227
00:14:12,810 --> 00:14:16,410
on my wedding day.

228
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:20,150
When that Yangban comes here,

229
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:21,240
it might be a bit hard at first,
since he's new here.

230
00:14:21,250 --> 00:14:25,840
But after that, donkeys loaded with meat
and rice will come every single day.

231
00:14:26,330 --> 00:14:29,990
We'll have meat soup and white rice every day.

232
00:14:30,310 --> 00:14:33,840
We'll eat our fill every single day.

233
00:14:34,710 --> 00:14:43,000
I want to try white rice too. Hot white rice.

234
00:14:44,820 --> 00:14:45,690
Me too.

235
00:14:46,160 --> 00:14:48,930
Oh dear, oh dear.

236
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:53,150
Mo-tong, I swear I'll get you white rice.

237
00:15:01,230 --> 00:15:02,820
Hey Gwangcheon!

238
00:15:07,010 --> 00:15:09,250
What's the Chief of
Gwangcheon Valley doing here?

239
00:15:10,460 --> 00:15:14,000
I heard something urgent happened
over on the other side of the mountain...

240
00:15:14,370 --> 00:15:16,980
no, over in Ansan.

241
00:15:17,490 --> 00:15:19,580
But why are you here?

242
00:15:20,080 --> 00:15:24,350
I came to the county office
to welcome another Yangban Lord.

243
00:15:24,540 --> 00:15:27,830
Ah, a Yangban Lord. I see.

244
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:29,240
-Is that guy with you? -What?

245
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:34,180
You bastard!

246
00:15:35,150 --> 00:15:36,330
Stop that thief!

247
00:15:39,870 --> 00:15:45,180
-Governor! Oh dear! -Governor! Governor!

248
00:15:45,190 --> 00:15:48,750
-Please hear me first.
-Me first please, Governor!

249
00:15:48,750 --> 00:15:50,650
Quiet!

250
00:15:50,660 --> 00:15:55,190
I'll speak quietly. Just listen.

251
00:15:55,340 --> 00:15:59,010
I'm one step ahead of him.
Please let me speak first.

252
00:15:59,010 --> 00:16:03,240
All right, all right. You go first.

253
00:16:03,250 --> 00:16:06,770
-But quietly. -Yes.

254
00:16:07,430 --> 00:16:12,350
Have you ever heard of Cheongnyeongpo,
deep in Gwangcheon Valley?

255
00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:14,300
What's Gwangcheon Valley?
And what's Cheongnyeongpo?

256
00:16:14,310 --> 00:16:16,560
You see, even you don't know it.

257
00:16:16,570 --> 00:16:18,790
That's how remote it is.

258
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:19,770
Within Yeongwol's territory,

259
00:16:19,770 --> 00:16:22,930
hidden deep in a mountain valley
is Gwangcheon Valley,

260
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:28,350
and the most secluded spot in
Gwangcheon Valley is Cheongnyeongpo.

261
00:16:28,350 --> 00:16:28,800
So?

262
00:16:29,020 --> 00:16:31,490
So what I'm saying is

263
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:35,440
Cheongnyeongpo is the perfect place for exile.

264
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:37,590
-Don't talk nonsense! -You!

265
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:43,330
The exile site in Yeongwol has
always been Norugol Valley.

266
00:16:43,340 --> 00:16:45,910
Everyone sent there has been very satisfied.

267
00:16:45,920 --> 00:16:48,280
Some even said they didn't want to leave.

268
00:16:48,300 --> 00:16:51,730
Changing the exile site all of a sudden
is absolutely unacceptable, Governor!

269
00:16:51,740 --> 00:16:53,900
I beg you to make a wise decision.

270
00:16:57,060 --> 00:16:57,590
Then

271
00:17:01,880 --> 00:17:02,950
the exile site

272
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:08,810
-shall be Norugol Valley. -Governor!

273
00:17:10,350 --> 00:17:11,460
Hey you!

274
00:17:11,600 --> 00:17:13,910
Governor! Governor!

275
00:17:13,920 --> 00:17:15,650
Please listen to me!

276
00:17:15,660 --> 00:17:18,160
I've heard enough.
Get lost! Didn't you hear me?

277
00:17:18,170 --> 00:17:19,590
Throw this bastard out immediately!

278
00:17:19,600 --> 00:17:23,010
-Please give Cheongnyeongpo one more chance!
-What's all this commotion?

279
00:17:28,010 --> 00:17:30,980
A madman is causing trouble here.
I'm throwing him out.

280
00:17:30,980 --> 00:17:32,810
That's not true. I'm not mad, My Lord!

281
00:17:33,160 --> 00:17:33,590
My Lord!

282
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:38,010
I am Eom Heung-do, former head of Yeongwol's household registry and now Chief of Gwangcheon Valley.

283
00:17:38,010 --> 00:17:40,120
What are you standing there for?
Throw him out right now!

284
00:17:40,260 --> 00:17:41,010
Stop.

285
00:17:47,530 --> 00:17:49,280
-Eom Heung do?
-Yes, yes!

286
00:17:49,470 --> 00:17:53,570
Tell me. Why do you want your village
to become an exile site?

287
00:18:00,740 --> 00:18:01,780
It is a place so remote
that badgers lose their way

288
00:18:01,790 --> 00:18:02,890
and raccoon dogs faint.

289
00:18:02,900 --> 00:18:05,950
An island within a land, Cheongnyeongpo.

290
00:18:13,830 --> 00:18:17,800
In summer, it is stifling hot and humid,

291
00:18:17,810 --> 00:18:21,140
swarming with dark mountain mosquitoes.

292
00:18:21,150 --> 00:18:23,610
In winter, the cold wind howls off the river

293
00:18:23,620 --> 00:18:25,810
and the chill from the cliffs bites down.

294
00:18:25,940 --> 00:18:29,190
It is a place where living itself feels like dying.

295
00:18:29,210 --> 00:18:32,210
I believe there is no better place for

296
00:18:32,460 --> 00:18:34,070
a man to repent his crimes.

297
00:18:34,750 --> 00:18:37,210
Having lived there long, from the moment

298
00:18:37,510 --> 00:18:39,630
I open my eyes in the morning
until I fall asleep at night...

299
00:18:56,500 --> 00:18:58,660
Set the exile site there.

300
00:19:01,410 --> 00:19:03,790
Thank you, My Lord! Thank you, My Lord!

301
00:19:04,290 --> 00:19:06,900
No matter who comes, can you handle it?

302
00:19:07,030 --> 00:19:13,090
Yes, of course. I can handle
whoever comes, My Lord!

303
00:19:14,110 --> 00:19:19,340
I will come to you again carrying a blade
in one hand and a reward in the other.

304
00:19:19,890 --> 00:19:24,070
Which one I give you
depends entirely on you.

305
00:19:24,220 --> 00:19:26,280
Yes, I will remember that.

306
00:19:26,430 --> 00:19:30,740
I will do everything
in my power to make it perfect.

307
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:43,080
Prince Nosan, the criminal. By royal decree:

308
00:19:45,090 --> 00:19:50,880
The treasonous conspiracy of Song Hyeon-su,
father-in-law of the Retired King, has come to light.

309
00:19:51,160 --> 00:19:57,290
The traitors Seong Sam-mun and
Bak Paeng-nyeon are executed by slow slicing.

310
00:19:58,180 --> 00:20:04,000
Grand Prince Geumseong, involved in
this treason, has been sentenced to exile

311
00:20:04,850 --> 00:20:08,440
Yet acts of rebellion,
great and small, have not ceased.

312
00:20:09,860 --> 00:20:17,750
Now Song Hyeon-su's treason
is fully revealed and undeniable.

313
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:21,240
Accordingly, the Retired King is
hereby demoted to Prince Nosan

314
00:20:21,240 --> 00:20:26,000
and exiled, so as to quiet public sentiment
and secure the stability of the kingdom.

315
00:20:55,250 --> 00:20:57,300
Are you just going to sit there?

316
00:20:57,750 --> 00:21:01,240
Hurry up! People can't work.
Put the roof tiles on.

317
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:02,340
So noisy.

318
00:21:02,370 --> 00:21:03,590
Oh, honestly.

319
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:07,340
A great man is coming from Hanyang.

320
00:21:07,350 --> 00:21:09,900
Not a single thing can go wrong.

321
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:13,200
Bring me a bowl of water.

322
00:21:13,210 --> 00:21:15,850
-What? This? -Yeah.

323
00:21:15,870 --> 00:21:16,950
Oh, come on.

324
00:21:18,700 --> 00:21:23,340
You heard her. Go! Hurry!

325
00:21:23,350 --> 00:21:27,020
-Hurry and carry it over. -Here.

326
00:21:28,570 --> 00:21:33,040
No time to drink water.
The Lord arrives any moment.

327
00:21:33,050 --> 00:21:35,330
Time is precious. No time to dawdle.

328
00:21:35,340 --> 00:21:36,900
No time for water!

329
00:21:39,620 --> 00:21:40,730
But, Grandpa.

330
00:21:41,570 --> 00:21:44,060
What was this place before?

331
00:21:44,070 --> 00:21:48,670
Ah, a shaman used to live here.

332
00:21:48,950 --> 00:21:50,380
-A shaman? -Creepy, right?

333
00:21:51,440 --> 00:21:55,270
-So never come in here again. Got it?
-Okay.

334
00:21:57,150 --> 00:21:59,690
Oh, you're still fooling around!

335
00:21:59,700 --> 00:22:00,420
Watch it!

336
00:22:00,430 --> 00:22:03,180
Didn't I say watch it?

337
00:22:03,720 --> 00:22:07,440
Do you know how much that one tile costs?

338
00:22:07,530 --> 00:22:08,630
-And... -Come down!

339
00:22:09,300 --> 00:22:11,730
-never grow up to be that kind of man.
-Get down!

340
00:22:11,730 --> 00:22:12,130
I won't.

341
00:22:12,740 --> 00:22:13,640
Get down!

342
00:22:15,550 --> 00:22:19,760
The raft is cleaned and ready.
Now we only await the Lord's arrival.

343
00:22:19,760 --> 00:22:23,380
Welcome, My Lord!
Please, this way, this way.

344
00:22:23,390 --> 00:22:24,950
Yes, this way.

345
00:22:26,070 --> 00:22:29,070
Oh dear. And donkeys, too.

346
00:22:29,420 --> 00:22:32,440
Sharp as always, My Lord. This way.

347
00:22:32,900 --> 00:22:35,990
Donkey, you can't come in.
Unload the baggage there.

348
00:22:35,990 --> 00:22:37,810
This way, My Lord!

349
00:22:40,640 --> 00:22:41,780
So scary.

350
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:48,560
You boy! You won't read, just fooling
around with that damn bow all day.

351
00:22:49,270 --> 00:22:54,010
Tae-san, you knew
the Thousand Character Classic at six,

352
00:22:54,020 --> 00:22:57,430
math at eight, and the Tonggam at ten.

353
00:22:57,540 --> 00:23:00,610
Why waste all that talent on this?

354
00:23:01,180 --> 00:23:01,960
Don't go on like this.

355
00:23:03,100 --> 00:23:05,480
It's not too late.
Prepare for the civil service exam.

356
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:13,340
Father, do you even know
what the exam really is?

357
00:23:14,750 --> 00:23:16,950
You think I don't want to take it?

358
00:23:17,320 --> 00:23:19,680
In this deep mountain,

359
00:23:19,680 --> 00:23:23,440
do we have the Four Books and the Three
Classics? Or a teacher who can teach me?

360
00:23:24,780 --> 00:23:28,260
There is a teacher. That Yangban Lord
is coming from Hanyang.

361
00:23:28,270 --> 00:23:33,600
A high official. Learn from him,
and you can take the exam.

362
00:23:33,850 --> 00:23:36,930
If you please him,
maybe you can even go to Hanyang.

363
00:23:37,670 --> 00:23:39,580
A Yangban would help us?

364
00:23:40,690 --> 00:23:42,570
Have you ever seen such a Yangban?

365
00:23:45,700 --> 00:23:46,330
So you wanna?

366
00:24:15,100 --> 00:24:17,540
Looks decent enough.

367
00:24:19,270 --> 00:24:20,620
Good work, everyone.

368
00:24:23,460 --> 00:24:25,780
But who's coming?

369
00:24:25,780 --> 00:24:28,540
The Chief put in so much effort.

370
00:24:28,550 --> 00:24:30,640
-Should be a good Yangban Lord. -You bet.

371
00:24:30,880 --> 00:24:32,760
I have a bad feeling.

372
00:24:33,170 --> 00:24:34,910
Probably another wasted effort.

373
00:24:34,920 --> 00:24:36,720
Don't start with that kind of talk.

374
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:39,890
Listen up, everyone.

375
00:24:39,900 --> 00:24:41,730
This is about life and death
for the village, right?

376
00:24:42,170 --> 00:24:45,510
Don't do anything foolish.
Even if the Yangban acts up,

377
00:24:45,520 --> 00:24:48,080
smile and bow.

378
00:24:48,090 --> 00:24:51,560
I see a horse. Someone's coming. Over there.

379
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:54,150
Quick, quick. Looks like they're here.

380
00:24:57,780 --> 00:24:58,980
The gold mine is here! Gold!

381
00:24:59,480 --> 00:25:02,150
Smile, everyone, smile!

382
00:25:12,750 --> 00:25:15,370
You expect me to cross
this river on this flimsy raft?

383
00:25:15,820 --> 00:25:17,000
Yes, My Lord.

384
00:25:17,480 --> 00:25:22,760
The sedan chair and the ladies will board.
The rest of you will swim across.

385
00:25:36,880 --> 00:25:38,060
What are you staring at?

386
00:25:42,980 --> 00:25:43,960
You row the raft.

387
00:25:44,680 --> 00:25:45,190
Yes, My Lord.

388
00:25:47,120 --> 00:25:48,190
Bring the sedan chair.

389
00:26:05,930 --> 00:26:08,580
-Where is the beard? -Ready!

390
00:26:08,660 --> 00:26:10,330
Ready!

391
00:26:10,680 --> 00:26:13,940
-Pull! -Let's go.

392
00:26:45,430 --> 00:26:47,230
The raft is drifting down.

393
00:26:48,470 --> 00:26:49,370
Pull harder!

394
00:26:57,110 --> 00:26:59,590
-Why isn't it moving?
-What's wrong?

395
00:26:59,850 --> 00:27:02,860
-What is it? -It's stuck again.

396
00:27:04,670 --> 00:27:07,930
It's stuck. Pull harder! Harder!

397
00:27:07,940 --> 00:27:10,350
-What are you standing there for?
-Damn it. Stuck on something.

398
00:27:10,640 --> 00:27:11,090
Pull together!

399
00:27:22,850 --> 00:27:23,470
Pull!

400
00:27:24,010 --> 00:27:25,950
Pull!

401
00:27:30,220 --> 00:27:31,250
Pull!

402
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:41,650
My Lord!

403
00:27:43,170 --> 00:27:43,660
My Lord!

404
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:45,760
Your Majesty!

405
00:27:50,560 --> 00:27:51,060
My Lord!

406
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:54,510
-Jump! What are you waiting for?
-Are you all right?

407
00:27:54,510 --> 00:27:57,100
-My Lord! -My Lord!

408
00:27:59,660 --> 00:28:01,810
Don't move. Don't move.

409
00:28:02,130 --> 00:28:03,960
Go! Hurry up! What are you doing?

410
00:28:16,680 --> 00:28:19,580
Come on, Tae-san. Try putting it here.

411
00:28:20,250 --> 00:28:20,850
Here?

412
00:28:20,910 --> 00:28:24,980
But the big-bearded Lord didn't come.

413
00:28:25,150 --> 00:28:27,790
Instead, a filthy little kid showed up.
What's going on?

414
00:28:28,520 --> 00:28:33,230
Right. What crime did such a young child
commit to be exiled like this?

415
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:38,460
Hey, Chief. What's that little Yangban's name?

416
00:28:38,860 --> 00:28:40,700
His name is Nosan. Nosan.

417
00:28:40,830 --> 00:28:41,930
What? Nosan?

418
00:28:43,370 --> 00:28:45,770
He probably won't last a month.

419
00:28:46,770 --> 00:28:47,810
A month?

420
00:28:48,710 --> 00:28:52,780
You mean Nosan will kill himself?

421
00:28:52,980 --> 00:28:54,150
Such a young boy,

422
00:28:54,980 --> 00:29:01,750
with no father, no subjects,
no palace, no throne.

423
00:29:03,020 --> 00:29:05,020
How could he endure?

424
00:29:06,660 --> 00:29:08,490
Well said.

425
00:29:14,200 --> 00:29:15,500
But don't forget,

426
00:29:18,100 --> 00:29:19,710
Grand Prince Geumseong, Nosan's uncle

427
00:29:19,870 --> 00:29:23,980
and the king's younger brother,

428
00:29:25,180 --> 00:29:27,550
is right there beside him.

429
00:29:28,680 --> 00:29:32,520
Sunheung
Exile Site of Grand Prince Geumseong

430
00:30:11,420 --> 00:30:12,360
Your Majesty,

431
00:30:13,730 --> 00:30:19,830
we swear to follow you to the death.

432
00:30:20,300 --> 00:30:22,530
-To the death! -To the death!

433
00:30:24,970 --> 00:30:29,740
I am most grateful.

434
00:30:36,680 --> 00:30:40,650
You're up? The meal is ready.

435
00:30:42,420 --> 00:30:44,820
Eom Heung-do, your Bosu Juin, requests an audience.
Bosu Juin: local officer in charge of
monitoring and caring for exiles

436
00:30:45,690 --> 00:30:49,060
It was such a mess just now.

437
00:30:49,090 --> 00:30:52,360
Damn raft got stuck on a rock.

438
00:30:52,800 --> 00:30:54,830
If I hadn't pushed with a pole,

439
00:30:54,900 --> 00:30:57,300
you'd have been swept downstream.

440
00:30:57,400 --> 00:30:58,840
Barely avoided disaster.

441
00:30:59,970 --> 00:31:03,210
To recover your strength, start with breakfast.

442
00:31:03,280 --> 00:31:06,110
The villagers prepared it with all their hearts.

443
00:31:06,580 --> 00:31:08,280
-Before it gets cold... -Leave us.

444
00:31:08,880 --> 00:31:09,550
What?

445
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:11,520
I said leave.

446
00:31:12,320 --> 00:31:13,320
Did he just say leave?

447
00:31:14,590 --> 00:31:18,060
His Lordship is in a bad mood.
You withdraw for now.

448
00:31:18,160 --> 00:31:19,420
I'm the Bosu Juin here.

449
00:31:19,460 --> 00:31:22,360
It is my duty to pay my respects in the morning and evening and to report to the government office.

450
00:31:22,460 --> 00:31:25,230
-I haven't even seen him, and he tells me to leave.
-Didn't he say leave?

451
00:31:25,430 --> 00:31:29,100
You dog! Didn't you hear me tell you to leave?

452
00:31:29,530 --> 00:31:31,570
Take the table and get lost!

453
00:31:32,100 --> 00:31:34,110
Quick, go!

454
00:31:38,710 --> 00:31:40,280
He's got a temper.

455
00:31:42,950 --> 00:31:44,980
Didn't you hear me say leave? Get lost!

456
00:31:45,380 --> 00:31:47,020
He called me a dog.

457
00:31:47,250 --> 00:31:51,460
Just because he's a Yangban,
a snot-nosed brat with no manners.

458
00:31:51,990 --> 00:31:53,630
How dare he speak to an elder like that?

459
00:31:56,430 --> 00:32:01,100
Forget it. Whatever he says, just smile.

460
00:32:01,130 --> 00:32:04,970
Smile, say yes, and bow.

461
00:32:04,970 --> 00:32:06,270
Really.

462
00:32:08,640 --> 00:32:12,310
Such delicious food. Why won't he eat?

463
00:32:18,380 --> 00:32:19,220
Oh my!

464
00:32:46,850 --> 00:32:49,150
At this rate, his cheeks are going to burst.

465
00:32:51,450 --> 00:32:53,590
It's a misunderstanding! Misunderstanding!

466
00:32:54,090 --> 00:32:56,190
I didn't eat because I wanted to.

467
00:32:56,460 --> 00:32:59,660
I found a bug this big in there.

468
00:32:59,690 --> 00:33:01,130
Misunderstanding!

469
00:33:12,640 --> 00:33:13,440
Governor!

470
00:33:13,840 --> 00:33:15,010
-Governor! -What?

471
00:33:15,840 --> 00:33:18,940
Why did the soldiers leave?

472
00:33:19,640 --> 00:33:20,650
You don't know?

473
00:33:20,980 --> 00:33:21,650
No.

474
00:33:22,180 --> 00:33:25,480
Guarding the exile site isn't the soldiers' job.

475
00:33:25,480 --> 00:33:26,890
It's the Bosu Juin's job.

476
00:33:26,950 --> 00:33:30,090
So don't forget to report on the first
and fifteenth of every month.

477
00:33:30,190 --> 00:33:32,220
Everything, big or small, must be reported.

478
00:33:32,490 --> 00:33:34,830
Yes, I understand.

479
00:33:45,040 --> 00:33:46,670
At least take this away.

480
00:33:49,610 --> 00:33:51,180
Honestly.

481
00:33:51,580 --> 00:33:54,150
Hey, did you hear?

482
00:33:54,480 --> 00:33:57,480
They say the Retired King
was exiled to Yeongwol.

483
00:33:57,580 --> 00:33:59,520
I heard something like that.

484
00:33:59,690 --> 00:34:02,290
Some place called
Cheongnyeongpo or something.

485
00:34:02,420 --> 00:34:03,420
Cheongnyeongpo?

486
00:34:10,430 --> 00:34:11,260
How is it?

487
00:34:11,430 --> 00:34:12,160
What?

488
00:34:12,160 --> 00:34:14,000
Does the food suit his taste?

489
00:34:15,630 --> 00:34:17,040
Didn't touch it.

490
00:34:17,140 --> 00:34:19,170
-What? -Didn't touch it at all?

491
00:34:19,200 --> 00:34:19,710
Nope.

492
00:34:19,810 --> 00:34:22,010
We saved that food for him.

493
00:34:22,040 --> 00:34:22,670
Seriously?

494
00:34:22,740 --> 00:34:24,610
Maybe he's unwell.

495
00:34:24,710 --> 00:34:26,610
Or maybe he has no appetite.

496
00:34:26,610 --> 00:34:28,280
No appetite?

497
00:34:29,110 --> 00:34:30,680
With food this precious?

498
00:34:30,680 --> 00:34:31,620
What's going on?

499
00:34:32,320 --> 00:34:33,690
And it's not like he didn't touch it,

500
00:34:33,820 --> 00:34:35,620
looks like someone already ate half.

501
00:34:35,690 --> 00:34:38,060
Well, he didn't eat. There's that maid.

502
00:34:38,060 --> 00:34:40,260
She ate it, and I caught her red-handed.

503
00:34:40,260 --> 00:34:41,890
But she swore she didn't.

504
00:34:41,890 --> 00:34:44,130
Her cheeks were so stuffed
they looked like they'd burst.

505
00:34:44,160 --> 00:34:45,060
Honestly.

506
00:34:50,540 --> 00:34:53,240
So can we give this to Mo-tong?

507
00:34:53,340 --> 00:34:54,070
Yeah.

508
00:34:54,870 --> 00:34:56,380
I never throw away leftovers.

509
00:34:58,080 --> 00:34:59,140
Mo-tong!

510
00:35:01,650 --> 00:35:03,020
He ate it.

511
00:35:03,080 --> 00:35:04,920
The bite marks match his teeth perfectly.

512
00:35:04,920 --> 00:35:06,020
Forget it.

513
00:35:06,950 --> 00:35:08,420
Gwangcheon.

514
00:35:11,260 --> 00:35:12,990
What brings you all the way here?

515
00:35:17,330 --> 00:35:18,230
Let's talk nicely.

516
00:35:18,300 --> 00:35:19,600
I understand how you feel,

517
00:35:19,700 --> 00:35:21,270
but that doesn't change the facts.

518
00:35:22,870 --> 00:35:24,600
I didn't come here to fight.

519
00:35:26,470 --> 00:35:29,670
This hen was raised on
nothing but good grain.

520
00:35:29,810 --> 00:35:30,640
Here, take it.

521
00:35:31,110 --> 00:35:32,780
Deodeok. Give him the deodeok too.

522
00:35:32,880 --> 00:35:35,180
-Here, fresh deodeok. Deodeok.
-What's this for?

523
00:35:35,180 --> 00:35:35,880
Why are you giving me this?

524
00:35:35,950 --> 00:35:39,550
You took the heat for me.
What's a hen compared to that?

525
00:35:40,250 --> 00:35:41,220
No, took what for you?

526
00:35:41,290 --> 00:35:45,160
This is our Norugol Valley specialty,
lion's mane mushroom.

527
00:35:45,160 --> 00:35:47,860
No, no. Why are you giving me all this?

528
00:35:48,360 --> 00:35:51,100
Thank you so much.

529
00:35:57,800 --> 00:36:02,040
Those lunatics said thank you
and left me all this stuff.

530
00:36:03,110 --> 00:36:03,740
Father.

531
00:36:04,340 --> 00:36:04,740
Yeah?

532
00:36:05,210 --> 00:36:07,210
Do you know who the exiled Yangban is?

533
00:36:07,410 --> 00:36:08,580
Yes. Nosan.

534
00:36:08,750 --> 00:36:11,250
Right. I'm asking if you know
who that Nosan really is.

535
00:36:11,350 --> 00:36:13,590
Yes. Nosan is Nosan.
Who else could he be?

536
00:36:13,690 --> 00:36:16,360
He's Prince Nosan Yi Hong-wi. Yi Hong-wi.

537
00:36:16,660 --> 00:36:20,630
Until recently, he was the king of this country.

538
00:36:21,230 --> 00:36:23,660
Did you eat something strange?

539
00:36:24,530 --> 00:36:25,260
What king?

540
00:36:25,460 --> 00:36:26,230
King.

541
00:36:26,870 --> 00:36:27,600
King?

542
00:36:27,800 --> 00:36:28,570
King.

543
00:36:29,600 --> 00:36:32,870
No matter who comes,
you can handle it?

544
00:36:33,810 --> 00:36:34,540
Your Majesty!

545
00:36:37,040 --> 00:36:38,580
-King? -King?

546
00:36:38,710 --> 00:36:40,280
You mean that boy was once the king?

547
00:36:40,450 --> 00:36:41,710
So I've heard.

548
00:36:41,750 --> 00:36:44,450
Wait. If he's a king, a king?

549
00:36:44,650 --> 00:36:46,850
Can a king be exiled?

550
00:36:47,620 --> 00:36:49,620
Can a Retired king be exiled?

551
00:36:49,650 --> 00:36:53,560
Look. Nosan became king through
succession from his father.

552
00:36:53,690 --> 00:36:57,360
But after his father died,
Grand Prince Suyang rebeled and became king.

553
00:36:57,360 --> 00:37:00,070
I heard that all the officials
who followed Nosan were executed.

554
00:37:00,070 --> 00:37:03,470
He was demoted to Prince Nosan and exiled here.

555
00:37:04,270 --> 00:37:08,640
But even so, they don't usually
exile a man who was once king.

556
00:37:08,640 --> 00:37:12,140
And there are many who pity him.

557
00:37:12,280 --> 00:37:14,010
Perhaps poison will be sent soon.

558
00:37:14,110 --> 00:37:15,810
-Poison? -Poison?

559
00:37:15,950 --> 00:37:18,120
That poison, you drink it and die, right?

560
00:37:18,220 --> 00:37:20,590
Then what happens to us?

561
00:37:21,150 --> 00:37:23,890
If something happens to Nosan, we...

562
00:37:24,390 --> 00:37:26,430
If something happens to the exiled,

563
00:37:29,060 --> 00:37:30,660
the exile territory will also face trouble.

564
00:37:30,760 --> 00:37:32,730
I heard that everyone who followed Nosan

565
00:37:32,730 --> 00:37:36,600
was dismembered, tortured to death.

566
00:37:36,640 --> 00:37:41,070
Their property confiscated. Children like Mo-tong
and Ae-dong were taken and sold.

567
00:37:41,170 --> 00:37:44,010
Oh my god!

568
00:37:44,540 --> 00:37:46,950
-What do we do? -What did I tell you?

569
00:37:47,150 --> 00:37:49,850
We're as good as dead now.

570
00:37:50,450 --> 00:37:53,590
It's all because of the Chief!

571
00:37:54,720 --> 00:37:55,990
As good as dead?

572
00:37:57,120 --> 00:37:59,860
What do you know? Stop yelling.

573
00:37:59,860 --> 00:38:03,730
I heard it clearly from
Lord Han Myong-hoe himself.

574
00:38:03,730 --> 00:38:07,370
Prince Nosan will soon return
to Hanyang and be restored.

575
00:38:07,470 --> 00:38:09,270
Are you telling the truth?

576
00:38:09,270 --> 00:38:10,900
You know me.

577
00:38:10,940 --> 00:38:12,770
I come from a distinguished family.

578
00:38:12,900 --> 00:38:16,680
Even with a sword at my throat, I never lie.

579
00:38:17,140 --> 00:38:18,410
That must be it.

580
00:38:20,050 --> 00:38:21,980
Just a rumor. A rumor.

581
00:38:55,550 --> 00:38:57,880
Your Majesty.

582
00:38:58,980 --> 00:39:01,420
Your Majesty.

583
00:39:01,590 --> 00:39:04,860
Your servant Seong Sam-mun...

584
00:39:07,860 --> 00:39:12,000
Why did you abandon us?

585
00:39:31,550 --> 00:39:33,620
Do not grieve too much.

586
00:39:36,960 --> 00:39:41,860
I will come to you soon.

587
00:39:44,860 --> 00:39:46,900
I never wanted fame or fortune.

588
00:39:47,030 --> 00:39:51,370
Just a bowl of white rice to live.

589
00:39:51,470 --> 00:39:56,540
I wanted my son to learn,
to live like a decent man.

590
00:39:56,810 --> 00:40:03,120
Of all the Yangbans, why does it have to be you?

591
00:40:03,220 --> 00:40:07,550
I begged everyone to have you here.

592
00:40:08,490 --> 00:40:14,560
I suffered so much for you.

593
00:40:20,270 --> 00:40:21,770
Why you, of all people, you scourge?

594
00:40:22,170 --> 00:40:23,870
Where have those scourges gone?

595
00:40:29,040 --> 00:40:30,110
It's a misunderstanding.

596
00:40:30,810 --> 00:40:34,150
I failed to recognize you before.

597
00:40:35,250 --> 00:40:38,250
But why are you here so late at night?

598
00:40:41,490 --> 00:40:44,160
It's dangerous there. That's a cliff.

599
00:40:47,790 --> 00:40:49,060
What are you doing?

600
00:40:51,300 --> 00:40:52,730
Come this way.

601
00:40:57,070 --> 00:40:58,340
No.

602
00:41:04,740 --> 00:41:06,550
Why are you doing this?

603
00:41:11,650 --> 00:41:13,290
Let go.

604
00:41:14,520 --> 00:41:15,690
Please.

605
00:41:17,090 --> 00:41:18,660
Let go of my hand.

606
00:41:19,690 --> 00:41:20,690
You must not.

607
00:41:21,060 --> 00:41:26,970
If you die, our whole village dies.

608
00:41:42,550 --> 00:41:43,820
Never mind.

609
00:41:45,120 --> 00:41:45,720
What?

610
00:41:47,520 --> 00:41:48,190
Yeah.

611
00:41:49,990 --> 00:41:50,860
What did you just say?

612
00:41:51,160 --> 00:41:54,330
The exile tried to kill himself.

613
00:41:54,330 --> 00:41:55,130
Who?

614
00:41:55,260 --> 00:41:56,160
Prince Nosan.

615
00:41:58,160 --> 00:42:01,270
Last night I went up to Yuryuk Peak
to check the waterway.

616
00:42:01,280 --> 00:42:03,600
I saw him about to jump off the cliff.

617
00:42:03,760 --> 00:42:04,560
Jump off a cliff?

618
00:42:04,560 --> 00:42:05,200
Yes.

619
00:42:06,160 --> 00:42:06,960
Then what?

620
00:42:06,960 --> 00:42:09,600
I ran over quickly and
barely managed to save him.

621
00:42:09,720 --> 00:42:12,080
If not for me, it would have been a disaster.

622
00:42:15,560 --> 00:42:18,920
Do not tell anyone
what happened yesterday. Understand?

623
00:42:18,920 --> 00:42:19,600
Yes.

624
00:42:19,880 --> 00:42:23,640
And you will closely monitor
every move of Prince Nosan.

625
00:42:23,840 --> 00:42:24,360
Yes.

626
00:42:24,960 --> 00:42:26,520
I will.

627
00:42:28,360 --> 00:42:29,040
Hey.

628
00:42:32,360 --> 00:42:33,120
What's that?

629
00:42:33,360 --> 00:42:34,640
Dried yellow croaker.

630
00:42:35,520 --> 00:42:36,960
White rice.

631
00:42:36,960 --> 00:42:38,800
Where did you get such precious things?

632
00:42:38,800 --> 00:42:41,640
From the coast. For the Lord.

633
00:42:41,640 --> 00:42:42,480
Tae-san.

634
00:42:42,600 --> 00:42:43,600
The Lord must be happy.

635
00:42:44,160 --> 00:42:46,120
Go and deliver it.

636
00:42:46,920 --> 00:42:47,520
Me?

637
00:42:47,720 --> 00:42:51,160
The Chief said he had official business at the county office, so he asked you to go instead.

638
00:43:00,320 --> 00:43:02,920
Who are you?

639
00:43:03,360 --> 00:43:06,920
I am Tae-san, son of Eom Heung-do,
Chief of Gwangcheon Village

640
00:43:07,640 --> 00:43:08,600
and Bosu Juin.

641
00:43:09,600 --> 00:43:11,200
Why are you standing there?
Why aren't you leaving?

642
00:43:11,400 --> 00:43:15,160
I have to watch you eat before I go.

643
00:43:19,440 --> 00:43:21,240
I hear you haven't eaten.

644
00:43:21,920 --> 00:43:24,200
I suppose a nobleman used to delicacies

645
00:43:25,360 --> 00:43:29,440
looks down on the food we eat just to survive.

646
00:43:30,360 --> 00:43:31,320
Insolent!

647
00:43:31,920 --> 00:43:33,080
Stop talking.

648
00:43:33,080 --> 00:43:35,480
If I bring back the untouched table,

649
00:43:35,720 --> 00:43:39,360
those who have nothing to eat
should be the angry ones.

650
00:43:39,520 --> 00:43:43,880
But instead, they worry whether you're unwell,

651
00:43:44,240 --> 00:43:48,440
or if the food doesn't suit you.

652
00:43:58,320 --> 00:44:02,120
Then you eat it.

653
00:44:13,960 --> 00:44:15,000
Any orders?

654
00:44:17,680 --> 00:44:18,960
Deliver a message.

655
00:44:19,480 --> 00:44:20,520
What?

656
00:44:22,800 --> 00:44:24,160
I ate well.

657
00:44:27,160 --> 00:44:27,920
Yes.

658
00:44:31,440 --> 00:44:33,840
Harder.

659
00:44:34,440 --> 00:44:36,680
One more time.

660
00:44:38,000 --> 00:44:39,240
I'm back.

661
00:44:39,720 --> 00:44:43,440
How did it go? Did he eat?

662
00:44:47,160 --> 00:44:49,280
Ate it all.

663
00:44:50,160 --> 00:44:51,000
All of it?

664
00:44:51,000 --> 00:44:51,560
Yeah.

665
00:44:51,560 --> 00:44:52,560
He finished it all?

666
00:44:52,560 --> 00:44:53,480
Yes.

667
00:44:54,320 --> 00:44:55,680
Strange.

668
00:44:55,840 --> 00:45:00,560
The Lord told me to tell everyone
that it was delicious.

669
00:45:00,560 --> 00:45:02,360
How grateful.

670
00:45:02,520 --> 00:45:05,120
He's got some warmth to him.

671
00:45:05,120 --> 00:45:06,240
Yes, human warmth.

672
00:45:09,160 --> 00:45:10,080
Yeah.

673
00:45:13,240 --> 00:45:16,120
I'll go next time. I'll go.

674
00:45:59,840 --> 00:46:01,600
What is this?

675
00:46:01,880 --> 00:46:04,440
A letter from Grand Prince Geumseong to you.

676
00:46:10,280 --> 00:46:12,880
Why don't you open it?

677
00:46:14,200 --> 00:46:15,040
My Lord.

678
00:46:17,000 --> 00:46:18,240
I'm afraid.

679
00:46:20,080 --> 00:46:26,080
I'm afraid of the letter's contents and the fact

680
00:46:27,920 --> 00:46:29,200
that it was delivered to me.

681
00:46:36,880 --> 00:46:38,760
That guy...

682
00:46:46,280 --> 00:46:47,760
What brings you here?

683
00:46:48,240 --> 00:46:51,280
Did you see Prince Nosan?

684
00:46:51,560 --> 00:46:52,320
No.

685
00:46:52,920 --> 00:46:54,080
Wasn't he in that house?

686
00:46:55,440 --> 00:46:56,480
He wasn't

687
00:46:57,360 --> 00:46:59,680
there when I got back from the county office.

688
00:46:59,960 --> 00:47:01,600
I searched everywhere.

689
00:47:02,080 --> 00:47:04,240
No sign of him.

690
00:47:05,520 --> 00:47:06,400
Then...

691
00:47:07,120 --> 00:47:08,400
Let go.

692
00:47:09,120 --> 00:47:10,800
Let go of my hand!

693
00:47:22,040 --> 00:47:25,200
Damn it! I tried so hard to save him!

694
00:47:27,800 --> 00:47:30,680
A letter from Grand Prince Geumseong to you.

695
00:47:57,640 --> 00:47:59,040
Do you want to die that badly?

696
00:48:00,360 --> 00:48:01,360
What did you say?

697
00:48:01,600 --> 00:48:05,200
The whole village is worried about you,
running around like crazy looking for you.

698
00:48:05,800 --> 00:48:07,920
And you only think about yourself, trying to die.

699
00:48:08,440 --> 00:48:10,600
Why are you so clueless?

700
00:48:10,880 --> 00:48:11,800
What?

701
00:48:12,520 --> 00:48:13,760
How dare you...

702
00:48:13,760 --> 00:48:16,320
Yes, yes. It's me.

703
00:48:16,520 --> 00:48:17,840
Are you out of your mind?

704
00:48:17,840 --> 00:48:18,760
Crazy. Crazy.

705
00:48:18,760 --> 00:48:20,840
How could I not be?

706
00:48:23,560 --> 00:48:25,760
To feed this village,

707
00:48:26,120 --> 00:48:27,760
to let my son study,

708
00:48:27,880 --> 00:48:30,480
I went through hell to
bring you here and serve you.

709
00:48:31,240 --> 00:48:33,880
And all you do is think about
jumping off a cliff and dying.

710
00:48:34,040 --> 00:48:36,560
How could I not be crazy?

711
00:48:36,760 --> 00:48:38,400
Aren't I right?

712
00:48:39,600 --> 00:48:40,600
You dog!

713
00:48:40,800 --> 00:48:41,920
What's going on?

714
00:48:42,320 --> 00:48:43,680
What are you doing?

715
00:48:43,680 --> 00:48:45,680
Careful! It's dangerous.

716
00:48:51,800 --> 00:48:53,160
Are you all right?

717
00:48:54,480 --> 00:48:55,240
Yeah.

718
00:48:55,360 --> 00:48:56,880
What happened?

719
00:48:56,880 --> 00:48:57,880
No idea.

720
00:49:05,920 --> 00:49:07,280
The king.

721
00:49:08,680 --> 00:49:09,920
The king is over there.

722
00:49:09,920 --> 00:49:12,880
Not that king. That king over there.

723
00:49:14,000 --> 00:49:15,400
What's wrong? What's wrong?

724
00:49:24,520 --> 00:49:26,760
Don't move.

725
00:49:27,040 --> 00:49:29,520
-What do we do? -Do something!

726
00:49:29,720 --> 00:49:32,760
Sorry.

727
00:49:32,880 --> 00:49:37,560
It takes only one person at a time.
Once it eats, it won't touch anyone else.

728
00:49:38,720 --> 00:49:41,240
-Where are you going? -Hey!

729
00:49:41,240 --> 00:49:42,840
I've lived long enough.

730
00:49:44,440 --> 00:49:46,080
Everyone stay healthy

731
00:49:46,200 --> 00:49:47,960
and live well.

732
00:49:49,000 --> 00:49:50,240
Here I go.

733
00:49:51,040 --> 00:49:52,960
Where are you going?

734
00:50:06,080 --> 00:50:08,720
Tae-san! Tae-san!

735
00:50:18,400 --> 00:50:19,720
You beast!

736
00:50:28,800 --> 00:50:32,000
I'm the one you're up against.

737
00:51:04,050 --> 00:51:06,050
My Lord!

738
00:51:07,440 --> 00:51:08,440
-My Lord! -My Lord!

739
00:51:10,280 --> 00:51:12,560
The tiger was killed by Nosan?

740
00:51:12,560 --> 00:51:13,320
That's right.

741
00:51:14,240 --> 00:51:16,680
It was a close call.

742
00:51:16,840 --> 00:51:18,200
My hands are still shaking.

743
00:51:18,200 --> 00:51:19,200
A close call.

744
00:51:19,480 --> 00:51:21,920
So this time, you saved Nosan again?

745
00:51:21,920 --> 00:51:22,920
No.

746
00:51:22,920 --> 00:51:27,000
This time, Prince Nosan
saved me and the village.

747
00:51:27,000 --> 00:51:30,080
Nonsense. Lying.

748
00:51:30,240 --> 00:51:31,600
I'm not lying.

749
00:51:31,600 --> 00:51:35,840
It's all true. Not a single word is a lie.

750
00:51:36,000 --> 00:51:39,600
Prince Nosan was like this.

751
00:51:41,600 --> 00:51:42,400
Stretching?

752
00:51:42,400 --> 00:51:47,400
No. Drawing a bow like this.

753
00:51:49,200 --> 00:51:50,080
Prince Nosan?

754
00:51:50,080 --> 00:51:51,440
No!

755
00:51:51,680 --> 00:51:54,520
Why would he roar! Damn it!

756
00:51:54,680 --> 00:51:58,400
Prince Nosan said, I'm the one

757
00:51:58,680 --> 00:51:59,640
you're up against.

758
00:51:59,920 --> 00:52:03,120
The tiger understood. I think it understood.

759
00:52:03,280 --> 00:52:07,240
As soon as he said it,
the tiger ran at him and roared.

760
00:52:07,240 --> 00:52:12,960
Then Prince Nosan shot his arrow.

761
00:52:13,400 --> 00:52:14,240
Hit.

762
00:52:14,240 --> 00:52:17,240
Hit, right between the eyes.

763
00:52:17,480 --> 00:52:19,960
The tiger fell off the cliff.

764
00:52:20,240 --> 00:52:21,360
Nosan...

765
00:52:26,080 --> 00:52:27,680
Incredible.

766
00:52:29,840 --> 00:52:31,440
After yesterday,

767
00:52:31,440 --> 00:52:33,280
now I can barely lift a spoon.

768
00:52:34,040 --> 00:52:37,560
I wonder how he's doing.

769
00:52:38,560 --> 00:52:39,800
So do I.

770
00:52:40,240 --> 00:52:42,640
He hasn't had a proper meal
since he got here.

771
00:52:42,880 --> 00:52:44,560
And then he collapsed yesterday.

772
00:52:44,560 --> 00:52:45,280
Yes, yes.

773
00:52:45,360 --> 00:52:48,880
Such a thin body yet such great courage.

774
00:52:49,280 --> 00:52:52,560
To step forward and risk his life against a tiger,

775
00:52:52,720 --> 00:52:55,000
only someone who truly cares for

776
00:52:55,080 --> 00:52:56,200
the people could do that.

777
00:52:56,200 --> 00:52:58,080
After all, he was once the king.

778
00:53:38,320 --> 00:53:40,720
Excuse me!

779
00:53:41,800 --> 00:53:43,760
Has the Lord woken up?

780
00:53:44,600 --> 00:53:45,760
Is he all right?

781
00:53:46,080 --> 00:53:47,080
Don't trouble yourself.

782
00:53:47,320 --> 00:53:48,440
Leave the table and go.

783
00:53:48,440 --> 00:53:53,120
At least let me see if he's alright.

784
00:53:53,120 --> 00:53:54,640
Didn't I say leave the table and go?

785
00:53:54,640 --> 00:53:59,000
Wait. Why are you so cold to me?

786
00:54:00,480 --> 00:54:02,240
Yesterday...

787
00:54:02,640 --> 00:54:03,480
What?

788
00:54:05,240 --> 00:54:06,760
Don't you remember
what you did yesterday?

789
00:54:07,120 --> 00:54:08,000
What?

790
00:54:10,840 --> 00:54:13,160
A man may lack learning

791
00:54:13,920 --> 00:54:15,760
but he should still know manners and limits.

792
00:54:15,880 --> 00:54:18,680
How dare you insult my lord
and grab his collar?

793
00:54:18,840 --> 00:54:20,320
How could you?

794
00:54:20,320 --> 00:54:23,800
Me? Grab his collar?

795
00:54:24,000 --> 00:54:26,400
I did this.

796
00:54:26,800 --> 00:54:29,280
And how do you know
if I have learning or not?

797
00:54:29,280 --> 00:54:30,720
Do I even need to ask?

798
00:54:30,720 --> 00:54:33,120
Even so, even if I have

799
00:54:33,120 --> 00:54:35,000
no learning,

800
00:54:35,200 --> 00:54:37,000
you don't say it to my face, do you?

801
00:54:37,000 --> 00:54:39,160
I don't want to talk to you. Go now.

802
00:54:43,520 --> 00:54:47,000
My Lord, are you all right?

803
00:54:47,880 --> 00:54:50,880
I'm hungry.

804
00:55:14,200 --> 00:55:16,560
Are you gonna wait until I finish eating?

805
00:55:16,800 --> 00:55:18,400
No. I'll take my leave.

806
00:55:19,720 --> 00:55:23,160
But, My Lord, if it weren't for you,

807
00:55:23,640 --> 00:55:25,440
my son and the villagers

808
00:55:25,600 --> 00:55:27,960
would have met a terrible fate.

809
00:55:27,960 --> 00:55:31,120
How can I repay this kindness?

810
00:55:31,760 --> 00:55:35,120
I worried about you all night.

811
00:55:35,680 --> 00:55:38,320
Let me at least see you eat a little before I go.

812
00:55:40,040 --> 00:55:43,320
If you permit, I'll wait outside.

813
00:55:44,640 --> 00:55:48,960
Your tone is different from yesterday.

814
00:55:51,280 --> 00:55:55,160
You're the first person to rage at me like that.

815
00:55:58,240 --> 00:55:59,520
My Lord.

816
00:55:59,760 --> 00:56:03,480
And you even grabbed my collar.

817
00:56:04,440 --> 00:56:05,880
When did I grab...

818
00:56:05,940 --> 00:56:07,050
Damn!

819
00:56:10,820 --> 00:56:11,620
What?

820
00:56:13,090 --> 00:56:14,220
What did you just say?

821
00:56:16,020 --> 00:56:17,060
Did I say something?

822
00:56:17,090 --> 00:56:18,960
You just said damn.

823
00:56:19,120 --> 00:56:20,260
When did I say damn?

824
00:56:22,390 --> 00:56:26,160
I was saying the Dawn, the starting point of
my new acquaintance with Your Lordship.

825
00:56:26,200 --> 00:56:28,630
How could I have said that curse word?

826
00:56:29,000 --> 00:56:31,170
That giant tiger truly

827
00:56:31,600 --> 00:56:32,740
was the very Dawn of it all.

828
00:56:32,740 --> 00:56:37,640
But what do you mean by
becoming the exile site?

829
00:56:37,910 --> 00:56:38,380
What?

830
00:56:38,580 --> 00:56:41,150
Yesterday on the mountain, didn't you say it?

831
00:56:41,250 --> 00:56:44,620
I absolutely cannot tell you.

832
00:56:51,390 --> 00:56:53,660
But the one who came was me.

833
00:56:53,890 --> 00:56:56,190
You were hoping for a Minister of Justice.

834
00:56:56,190 --> 00:57:00,600
Instead, I came, no connections to send donkey caravans of gifts, no way to advance anyone's career.

835
00:57:03,640 --> 00:57:06,470
Is that so funny?

836
00:57:07,510 --> 00:57:11,780
I imagined how you must have felt
when you learned who I really am.

837
00:57:13,780 --> 00:57:17,220
I honestly didn't expect it
to be so complicated.

838
00:57:20,350 --> 00:57:21,190
But here I am.

839
00:57:22,720 --> 00:57:25,420
Far from filling the villagers' bellies,

840
00:57:26,690 --> 00:57:28,360
I've only been consuming what you provide.

841
00:57:29,030 --> 00:57:30,160
You're too kind.

842
00:57:30,860 --> 00:57:35,670
As long as you eat happily, that is enough.

843
00:57:47,110 --> 00:57:48,780
He's here! He's here!

844
00:57:51,750 --> 00:57:53,920
How is Prince Nosan?

845
00:57:55,320 --> 00:57:57,320
What's wrong? Why are you sighing?

846
00:57:58,160 --> 00:57:59,960
One bowl of rice.

847
00:57:59,960 --> 00:58:01,790
He ate it all in one go.

848
00:58:03,760 --> 00:58:04,600
Look at you, so startled.

849
00:58:04,630 --> 00:58:07,000
It must have suited his taste.

850
00:58:07,000 --> 00:58:09,740
What did I tell you?
That's the spirit of a king.

851
00:58:10,270 --> 00:58:11,400
Look at you being scared.

852
00:58:12,900 --> 00:58:15,870
But he asked about you.

853
00:58:17,410 --> 00:58:18,780
He asked about me?

854
00:58:26,320 --> 00:58:28,650
Who made this soup?

855
00:58:28,920 --> 00:58:34,090
I got up before dawn and caught
freshwater snails from Dongjiang River.

856
00:58:34,090 --> 00:58:35,430
You cooked it yourself?

857
00:58:36,330 --> 00:58:39,030
No, I caught them myself.

858
00:58:39,130 --> 00:58:41,530
I asked who made the soup.

859
00:58:41,630 --> 00:58:43,740
Her cooking is even better than
the royal kitchen's head court lady.

860
00:58:44,270 --> 00:58:48,300
It's Mo-tong Mom. She's a good cook.

861
00:58:48,300 --> 00:58:50,140
Though sometimes there's hair...

862
00:58:50,240 --> 00:58:53,080
Is she called Mo-tong Mom
because she's Mo-tong's mother?

863
00:58:53,250 --> 00:58:56,480
Yes. Mo-tong is young,

864
00:58:56,780 --> 00:58:59,690
but very clever and capable.

865
00:59:00,450 --> 00:59:02,350
Oh, and this porridge

866
00:59:03,560 --> 00:59:08,730
is made from river fish
the kid caught in a fish trap.

867
00:59:12,130 --> 00:59:15,770
And these pancakes,
they have mountain pepper,

868
00:59:15,800 --> 00:59:19,440
picked by the oldest elder
in the village from the Yuryuk Peak cliff.

869
00:59:19,600 --> 00:59:24,940
And this meat, Long caught a rabbit.

870
00:59:24,940 --> 00:59:27,350
The wild ginseng root sprinkled on top

871
00:59:27,450 --> 00:59:32,350
was treasured by Mo-tong's father.

872
00:59:32,450 --> 00:59:35,350
The raspberries are from a widow
named Cheongsan of Icheon family.

873
00:59:35,690 --> 00:59:38,060
She picked them from
a place full of snakes.

874
00:59:39,560 --> 00:59:40,330
I see.

875
00:59:40,360 --> 00:59:45,630
But all of this was done
under my strict and careful direction.

876
00:59:45,930 --> 00:59:48,630
I must make that clear

877
00:59:49,130 --> 00:59:51,100
The snails were caught by me personally.

878
00:59:53,510 --> 00:59:55,610
All right. I see.

879
00:59:57,500 --> 01:00:02,010
I noticed you only asked about the person who made it, not the ingredients.

880
01:00:02,310 --> 01:00:04,580
I caught this before dawn myself.

881
01:00:05,050 --> 01:00:06,950
Alright, I'll remember that.

882
01:00:15,930 --> 01:00:21,330
Oh my, the King actually mentioned my name.

883
01:00:21,370 --> 01:00:24,900
Your Highness is so young, yet you already understand women's hearts.

884
01:00:26,540 --> 01:00:29,740
What “Your Highness”? Don't call me that anymore.

885
01:00:29,840 --> 01:00:32,540
Just call me Nosan, or Prince Nosan.

886
01:00:32,640 --> 01:00:34,010
There are no outsiders here anyway.

887
01:00:34,110 --> 01:00:36,520
Does it really matter whether you call him Your Highness or Prince?

888
01:00:36,520 --> 01:00:37,620
Right?

889
01:00:38,020 --> 01:00:39,720
You could tell from the way he faced that tiger.

890
01:00:40,090 --> 01:00:41,750
A king indeed lives up to his title.

891
01:00:43,520 --> 01:00:45,560
If someone hears you, it'll be trouble. Don't keep calling him King.

892
01:00:45,660 --> 01:00:49,090
Chief, someone's coming over there.

893
01:00:59,200 --> 01:01:02,310
Do you know where Cheongnyeongpo is?

894
01:01:02,410 --> 01:01:03,710
This way…

895
01:01:05,680 --> 01:01:06,750
Who are you people?

896
01:01:08,380 --> 01:01:12,450
We came from Haeju in Hwanghae Province to pay respects to His Highness…

897
01:01:13,650 --> 01:01:16,090
We came to see Prince Nosan.

898
01:01:16,220 --> 01:01:17,420
Hwanghae Province…

899
01:01:19,390 --> 01:01:20,190
But why

900
01:01:21,030 --> 01:01:22,190
have you come to see him?

901
01:01:22,290 --> 01:01:23,860
Your Highness…

902
01:01:23,960 --> 01:01:24,730
Your Highness…

903
01:01:24,800 --> 01:01:26,300
Your Highness…

904
01:01:26,730 --> 01:01:31,270
How could such a bolt from the blue happen?

905
01:01:32,440 --> 01:01:37,840
We, your unworthy subjects who failed to serve you,

906
01:01:37,940 --> 01:01:40,180
please forgive us.

907
01:01:40,310 --> 01:01:42,080
You mustn't call him “Your Highness.”

908
01:01:42,280 --> 01:01:44,320
If the authorities hear it, it'll be trouble.

909
01:01:44,420 --> 01:01:46,620
Your Highness…

910
01:01:46,850 --> 01:01:47,850
You mustn't call him that.

911
01:01:49,090 --> 01:01:51,420
Stop them, don't let them go down.

912
01:01:51,820 --> 01:01:53,390
You mustn't call him “Your Highness.”

913
01:01:53,490 --> 01:01:54,830
Your Highness…

914
01:01:54,830 --> 01:01:56,960
I said don't call him that.

915
01:01:57,160 --> 01:01:58,660
Your Highness…

916
01:01:58,660 --> 01:02:01,670
You can cry, but you mustn't call him “Your Highness.”

917
01:02:02,400 --> 01:02:03,300
You can cry.

918
01:02:03,400 --> 01:02:04,970
Please accept this.

919
01:02:05,070 --> 01:02:07,770
Stop, stop!

920
01:02:33,700 --> 01:02:34,930
Raise your head.

921
01:02:39,910 --> 01:02:41,510
Was the letter delivered?

922
01:02:41,610 --> 01:02:45,180
As you ordered, I personally handed it to the court lady, Your Highness.

923
01:02:49,980 --> 01:02:51,650
Go to Yeongwol again.

924
01:02:51,650 --> 01:02:57,420
Hang a white garment on the tree of Mt. Cheomgak, directly across from His Highness's residence.

925
01:02:57,660 --> 01:03:01,390
Then His Highness will tie a reply to an arrow and shoot it back.

926
01:03:01,790 --> 01:03:03,460
Yes, Grand Prince.

927
01:03:05,060 --> 01:03:06,230
They just keep drifting in endlessly.

928
01:03:06,330 --> 01:03:07,230
Be careful.

929
01:03:11,570 --> 01:03:12,640
Village chief.

930
01:03:12,900 --> 01:03:15,770
How did you come up with such a brilliant idea?

931
01:03:16,780 --> 01:03:18,340
Truly admirable.

932
01:03:19,280 --> 01:03:22,210
Alright, we can haul in the net now.

933
01:03:24,080 --> 01:03:26,590
Let me see what treasures we've got.

934
01:03:27,820 --> 01:03:28,920
What's this?

935
01:03:31,090 --> 01:03:33,430
Ginseng, ginseng!

936
01:03:38,430 --> 01:03:40,130
And dried yellow croaker.

937
01:03:40,230 --> 01:03:41,930
Bigger than my palm.

938
01:03:42,030 --> 01:03:43,840
Look, dried meat!

939
01:03:44,700 --> 01:03:45,940
What's this?

940
01:03:47,370 --> 01:03:48,470
Didn't I tell you?

941
01:03:48,510 --> 01:03:53,480
Even without a caravan, we won't go hungry anymore.

942
01:03:53,580 --> 01:03:55,580
Didn't I say so?

943
01:03:55,680 --> 01:03:56,720
You did.

944
01:03:56,850 --> 01:03:58,420
Not just anyone can be a village chief.

945
01:03:58,520 --> 01:04:02,420
I've always believed in our village chief.

946
01:04:03,090 --> 01:04:04,490
How shameless.

947
01:04:08,830 --> 01:04:10,130
That startled me.

948
01:04:10,430 --> 01:04:12,330
It's so late. What brings you here?

949
01:04:20,970 --> 01:04:21,740
Sir.

950
01:04:23,340 --> 01:04:24,380
The prince has arrived.

951
01:04:24,440 --> 01:04:27,650
The prince is here! The prince is here! Sir!

952
01:04:32,120 --> 01:04:33,450
Why so flustered?

953
01:04:33,820 --> 01:04:35,820
As if you've seen a ghost.

954
01:04:35,820 --> 01:04:37,960
Who is that man?

955
01:04:38,360 --> 01:04:40,290
Mo-tong, you can't speak like that.

956
01:04:43,660 --> 01:04:46,060
My name is Yi Hong-wi.

957
01:04:46,160 --> 01:04:49,000
So you're the one who catches fish with fish traps.

958
01:04:49,970 --> 01:04:50,570
Alright.

959
01:04:53,510 --> 01:04:54,570
Mo-tong…

960
01:04:55,310 --> 01:04:56,880
She's Granny Icheon.

961
01:04:56,880 --> 01:04:57,710
Granny Icheon.

962
01:04:57,780 --> 01:04:58,780
Raspberries.

963
01:05:01,010 --> 01:05:04,020
Raspberries, raspberries. The ones I picked a whole bowl of.

964
01:05:05,480 --> 01:05:07,850
So you're the Granny Icheon who picks raspberries.

965
01:05:07,850 --> 01:05:09,150
Yes, sir.

966
01:05:09,150 --> 01:05:10,490
She's Mo-tong's mother.

967
01:05:10,590 --> 01:05:12,520
So you're the one who cooks the food, Mo-tong's mother.

968
01:05:12,520 --> 01:05:13,330
Yes.

969
01:05:15,060 --> 01:05:17,830
The ginseng you sent tastes excellent, Mo-tong's father.

970
01:05:18,100 --> 01:05:20,700
I'm Mo-tong's father.

971
01:05:20,970 --> 01:05:24,270
Then the one who catches rabbits is…

972
01:05:24,370 --> 01:05:26,510
Sir, that's me, Long.

973
01:05:26,510 --> 01:05:28,640
I hear you run very fast.

974
01:05:28,940 --> 01:05:33,810
When this kid runs, no one in Yeongwol can catch him.

975
01:05:35,080 --> 01:05:38,480
The mountain peppers you sent have a superb spicy flavor.

976
01:05:39,690 --> 01:05:41,550
Though drying them is a bit troublesome.

977
01:05:42,320 --> 01:05:44,790
By the way, what are these behind?

978
01:05:44,790 --> 01:05:50,360
These are all food sent to you by the villagers.

979
01:05:50,760 --> 01:05:52,600
Before giving them to you,

980
01:05:52,730 --> 01:05:56,540
we were just checking if any had gone bad.

981
01:05:56,540 --> 01:05:59,140
We didn't take any, please rest assured.

982
01:06:01,470 --> 01:06:02,210
No.

983
01:06:05,140 --> 01:06:07,210
Since these have been delivered to Gwangcheon Valley,

984
01:06:08,580 --> 01:06:09,880
they should belong to you.

985
01:06:12,080 --> 01:06:13,720
Such precious food for you, sir...

986
01:06:13,750 --> 01:06:15,250
We must be crazy, how could we…

987
01:06:26,530 --> 01:06:28,800
What a generous heart.

988
01:06:29,200 --> 01:06:32,140
I want to learn to read and write.

989
01:06:33,210 --> 01:06:34,910
Please be my teacher.

990
01:06:36,610 --> 01:06:40,850
I heard you usually have no interest in studying.

991
01:06:42,750 --> 01:06:46,720
Why the change of heart?

992
01:06:48,350 --> 01:06:50,220
For a rustic commoner like me,

993
01:06:51,160 --> 01:06:53,490
I want to study but have no books to seek.

994
01:06:54,130 --> 01:06:56,190
I want to learn but have no teacher to follow.

995
01:06:56,190 --> 01:06:57,260
Even if I did learn,

996
01:06:58,860 --> 01:07:01,470
I would still feel there's no hope of passing the exams.

997
01:07:04,200 --> 01:07:10,640
But if I were taught by someone like you,

998
01:07:10,940 --> 01:07:15,910
I believe I could break through that slim chance.

999
01:07:16,880 --> 01:07:20,490
So I wish to enter the court and bring change,

1000
01:07:21,490 --> 01:07:25,190
to create a world where even those with no connections,
ignorant country folk, even commoners and servants,

1001
01:07:26,790 --> 01:07:31,830
can have a fair chance.

1002
01:07:34,500 --> 01:07:37,370
A world of fair opportunity…

1003
01:07:44,380 --> 01:07:44,980
Alright.

1004
01:07:47,450 --> 01:07:48,750
Then let's give it a try.

1005
01:07:50,550 --> 01:07:52,850
Virtue is not left to stand alone; it always attracts companions.

1006
01:07:53,520 --> 01:07:56,120
A person of virtue is never alone,

1007
01:07:56,190 --> 01:07:58,790
they will surely have like-minded friends.

1008
01:07:59,160 --> 01:08:00,430
Over there, over there!

1009
01:08:00,560 --> 01:08:02,430
-Put it here. -Put it here!

1010
01:08:02,560 --> 01:08:03,330
Oh my.

1011
01:08:06,870 --> 01:08:07,470
Come.

1012
01:08:09,900 --> 01:08:11,540
Such boundless grace.

1013
01:08:12,200 --> 01:08:14,540
They say the fish head is the tastiest part. Please enjoy it.

1014
01:08:16,910 --> 01:08:19,140
Keep the good things.

1015
01:08:20,350 --> 01:08:23,120
Even if I'm unlearned, I can't do that.

1016
01:08:23,120 --> 01:08:25,420
Such precious food. Let's share it together.

1017
01:08:28,650 --> 01:08:31,520
Write these characters with me.

1018
01:08:31,890 --> 01:08:33,830
“Yu” as in house, “Zhou” as in all time past and present.

1019
01:08:33,860 --> 01:08:36,090
“Yu” as in house, “Zhou” as in all time past and present.

1020
01:08:36,090 --> 01:08:37,860
“Hong” as in flood, “Huang” as in desolation.

1021
01:08:37,930 --> 01:08:39,630
“Hong” as in flood, “Huang” as in desolation.

1022
01:08:39,630 --> 01:08:41,400
You wouldn't believe how much came.

1023
01:08:41,470 --> 01:08:44,140
Everyone was stunned.

1024
01:08:44,240 --> 01:08:46,440
They brought a whole pile of things.

1025
01:08:46,540 --> 01:08:48,710
I just went over and tapped it.

1026
01:08:49,780 --> 01:08:53,650
This bowstring is made from silk spun by silkworms that eat mulberry leaves.

1027
01:08:53,750 --> 01:08:56,950
Its toughness is unmatched by other bowstrings.

1028
01:08:59,890 --> 01:09:02,790
The one who made the lacquered bow is a servant.

1029
01:09:03,220 --> 01:09:08,360
My grandfather and father both took pride in learning from him.

1030
01:09:09,060 --> 01:09:13,340
Learning knows no rank. Status doesn't matter.

1031
01:09:14,200 --> 01:09:14,870
What?

1032
01:09:16,120 --> 01:09:16,790
Move aside.

1033
01:09:18,220 --> 01:09:18,820
Where for me to go?

1034
01:09:21,060 --> 01:09:24,660
On the night before the wedding, you must not share a room…

1035
01:09:33,940 --> 01:09:37,370
A wild boar charged at me.

1036
01:09:40,580 --> 01:09:42,940
Mo-tong, which one do you think is better?

1037
01:09:42,940 --> 01:09:43,910
This one?

1038
01:09:45,180 --> 01:09:46,920
Mo-tong can write too?

1039
01:09:46,950 --> 01:09:48,080
Did I write it correctly?

1040
01:09:48,600 --> 01:09:49,990
That's right, that's right. Our Mo-tong did well.

1041
01:09:50,420 --> 01:09:52,290
Dad, I hung it up.

1042
01:09:52,390 --> 01:09:53,560
Well done.

1043
01:09:53,560 --> 01:09:54,690
It looks great.

1044
01:09:56,260 --> 01:09:57,660
Over here. This spot works.

1045
01:09:57,990 --> 01:09:59,630
Is this okay?

1046
01:10:21,600 --> 01:10:24,390
Our Mo-tong is really amazing.

1047
01:10:31,070 --> 01:10:31,840
I heard

1048
01:10:32,250 --> 01:10:34,080
Nosan fought a tiger.

1049
01:10:35,190 --> 01:10:37,050
Someone as timid as a mouse?

1050
01:10:38,480 --> 01:10:42,130
That must be some ridiculous story made up by those who love to exaggerate.

1051
01:10:42,380 --> 01:10:43,790
Who would believe it?

1052
01:10:47,760 --> 01:10:50,770
Their negligence is what allowed us to seize power.

1053
01:10:51,980 --> 01:10:54,670
If left to grow, it will become a great tree in no time.

1054
01:10:58,670 --> 01:10:59,310
You

1055
01:11:00,330 --> 01:11:02,380
keep a close watch on Grand Prince.

1056
01:11:03,410 --> 01:11:04,560
I will go to Yeongwol.

1057
01:11:07,330 --> 01:11:10,920
His Highness will surely be comforted by your loyalty.

1058
01:11:11,300 --> 01:11:11,940
Your Highness…

1059
01:11:12,770 --> 01:11:15,270
The time to set history right has finally come.

1060
01:11:16,240 --> 01:11:17,320
I, Geumseong,

1061
01:11:17,840 --> 01:11:19,180
together with Prefect Lee Bu-geun,

1062
01:11:19,930 --> 01:11:21,230
Governor Ryu Gi-san of Anju,

1063
01:11:22,120 --> 01:11:23,850
and Vice Director Jo Yu-rye and others,

1064
01:11:24,430 --> 01:11:25,960
are planning an uprising.

1065
01:11:27,070 --> 01:11:29,930
The local magistrates are also of one mind.

1066
01:11:31,270 --> 01:11:31,790
However,

1067
01:11:32,750 --> 01:11:33,960
without Your Highness's approval,

1068
01:11:34,600 --> 01:11:36,840
we dare not act rashly.

1069
01:11:37,780 --> 01:11:46,090
We earnestly request Your Highness to grant us a reply of consent.

1070
01:12:07,940 --> 01:12:10,310
You say the letter delivered to Nosan...

1071
01:12:11,070 --> 01:12:12,800
Its sender is Grand Prince Geumseong?

1072
01:12:14,590 --> 01:12:15,100
Speak.

1073
01:12:16,120 --> 01:12:17,790
What is written in the letter?

1074
01:12:18,490 --> 01:12:21,950
You rose to high office by

1075
01:12:23,160 --> 01:12:25,150
fabricating history with nothing but false merit.

1076
01:12:25,910 --> 01:12:28,220
Would someone like you care about the truth?

1077
01:12:33,230 --> 01:12:35,400
As the family of a traitor,

1078
01:12:36,430 --> 01:12:37,710
the fate is either exile

1079
01:12:38,410 --> 01:12:39,630
or becoming slaves.

1080
01:12:43,000 --> 01:12:45,310
But I will do it myself.

1081
01:12:46,740 --> 01:12:48,210
I will tear your family to pieces

1082
01:12:49,810 --> 01:12:51,620
and scatter them across the provinces.

1083
01:12:51,620 --> 01:12:53,280
Han Myong-heo, you wretch...

1084
01:12:53,670 --> 01:12:55,710
Never in all eternity

1085
01:12:56,030 --> 01:12:58,270
has there been such a criminal who defiles the state.

1086
01:13:02,280 --> 01:13:04,460
Anyone who communicates with Nosan

1087
01:13:05,740 --> 01:13:07,720
must be executed.

1088
01:13:11,630 --> 01:13:12,910
He's gone missing.

1089
01:13:13,230 --> 01:13:13,680
Yes.

1090
01:13:14,130 --> 01:13:17,330
He was sent to Yeongwol on the Grand Prince's orders several days ago.

1091
01:13:17,460 --> 01:13:19,760
Not only has he not returned, there's not even any news.

1092
01:13:24,430 --> 01:13:25,580
You go to Yeongwol.

1093
01:13:26,800 --> 01:13:28,210
Go and check the mark.

1094
01:13:28,410 --> 01:13:29,420
Yes, Your Highness.

1095
01:13:36,140 --> 01:13:39,280
From today onward, tighten security around the exile's residence.

1096
01:13:39,660 --> 01:13:41,010
This is an order from the court.

1097
01:13:41,580 --> 01:13:45,620
Four men in front will guard the gate in shifts day and night.

1098
01:13:46,060 --> 01:13:48,930
Four men in the back will patrol the residence.

1099
01:13:49,310 --> 01:13:52,600
From now on, we will strictly guard the exile's residence.

1100
01:13:52,830 --> 01:13:53,280
Yes.

1101
01:13:57,120 --> 01:13:57,890
Where are you going?

1102
01:13:58,270 --> 01:13:59,980
Prince Nosan has nightmares every night.

1103
01:13:59,980 --> 01:14:01,450
I heard gastrodia helps,

1104
01:14:01,580 --> 01:14:02,410
so I'm going to dig some up.

1105
01:14:03,180 --> 01:14:04,580
You care more about him than your own son.

1106
01:14:05,450 --> 01:14:06,600
If there's any left, give me some too.

1107
01:14:07,490 --> 01:14:08,200
What do you need it for?

1108
01:14:08,770 --> 01:14:09,600
Do you have nightmares too?

1109
01:14:09,790 --> 01:14:11,390
Of course I do.

1110
01:14:12,030 --> 01:14:13,190
Terrifying nightmares.

1111
01:14:13,510 --> 01:14:14,270
I dream about my father.

1112
01:14:16,610 --> 01:14:17,260
You brat.

1113
01:14:17,840 --> 01:14:19,310
You dreamed of your father.

1114
01:14:19,630 --> 01:14:20,960
Why call it a nightmare?

1115
01:14:20,960 --> 01:14:22,490
That's a good omen, you fool.

1116
01:14:22,960 --> 01:14:24,560
What is this?

1117
01:14:25,550 --> 01:14:25,930
This...

1118
01:14:27,080 --> 01:14:28,960
It's essays the village children wrote using proverbs.

1119
01:14:29,690 --> 01:14:31,660
Prince Nosan said he wanted to see them,

1120
01:14:31,660 --> 01:14:33,460
so I brought them from the children.

1121
01:14:34,220 --> 01:14:35,820
Take them to him.

1122
01:14:35,890 --> 01:14:38,580
After seeing them, he'll surely be very pleased.

1123
01:14:39,560 --> 01:14:40,900
You're really something.

1124
01:14:43,120 --> 01:14:43,950
Take care, Father.

1125
01:14:44,090 --> 01:14:44,660
Alright.

1126
01:15:01,710 --> 01:15:03,410
What are you hunting this time,

1127
01:15:03,610 --> 01:15:05,150
drawing the bow so tight?

1128
01:15:07,600 --> 01:15:11,180
I'm aiming at my own weak and foolish self,

1129
01:15:12,330 --> 01:15:13,740
who failed to protect my people.

1130
01:15:14,170 --> 01:15:16,620
You call yourself weak, sir?

1131
01:15:17,070 --> 01:15:19,370
If you were weak, how could you kill a tiger,

1132
01:15:19,560 --> 01:15:20,970
such a huge one at that?

1133
01:15:21,100 --> 01:15:23,850
And if you were foolish, how could you teach the illiterate to write,

1134
01:15:23,850 --> 01:15:25,770
and do it so well?

1135
01:15:26,730 --> 01:15:31,720
So, sir, you are neither weak nor foolish.

1136
01:15:33,170 --> 01:15:33,620
Yes…

1137
01:15:34,510 --> 01:15:35,920
Now that you say it, that's true.

1138
01:15:37,400 --> 01:15:38,870
Of course it is.

1139
01:15:39,230 --> 01:15:42,430
Just a moment. I came to see the village chief. Just a moment.

1140
01:15:42,430 --> 01:15:43,580
-Village chief. -Long!

1141
01:15:44,350 --> 01:15:47,020
-Tae-san has been taken to the authorities. -What?

1142
01:15:47,160 --> 01:15:49,850
Wait, wait, village chief!

1143
01:15:56,380 --> 01:15:57,080
Stop!

1144
01:15:58,690 --> 01:16:00,480
I've come to see the Governor.

1145
01:16:00,870 --> 01:16:02,340
Please… let me go in.

1146
01:16:02,910 --> 01:16:04,960
-Where do you think this is? -Let me in!

1147
01:16:05,330 --> 01:16:07,120
I came to see the Governor.

1148
01:16:09,300 --> 01:16:11,990
Eleven strokes.

1149
01:16:12,500 --> 01:16:14,680
Twelve strokes.

1150
01:16:15,530 --> 01:16:17,380
-Thirteen. -Tae-san. Tae-san.

1151
01:16:17,380 --> 01:16:18,610
No, no!

1152
01:16:21,540 --> 01:16:22,860
-What's going on? -Father!

1153
01:16:23,410 --> 01:16:25,910
What on earth is happening?

1154
01:16:25,910 --> 01:16:28,590
I heard someone was entering and leaving the exile's residence without permission,

1155
01:16:28,910 --> 01:16:30,190
so I had him arrested.

1156
01:16:31,280 --> 01:16:32,750
He is my son.

1157
01:16:33,070 --> 01:16:34,420
He did not go in and out without permission.

1158
01:16:34,680 --> 01:16:36,590
I sent him.

1159
01:16:36,590 --> 01:16:39,730
I said that except for the appointed guardian, no one may enter or leave the place of exile.

1160
01:16:40,370 --> 01:16:42,030
One hundred strokes of the rod.

1161
01:16:45,750 --> 01:16:47,030
Since I sent him,

1162
01:16:47,350 --> 01:16:48,370
I will take the punishment.

1163
01:16:48,830 --> 01:16:51,630
Please release my son.

1164
01:16:52,180 --> 01:16:53,270
What are you all standing for?

1165
01:16:53,270 --> 01:16:55,320
Take this ignorant fool away.

1166
01:16:55,560 --> 01:16:56,450
Yes.

1167
01:16:56,850 --> 01:16:58,190
Please let my son go.

1168
01:16:58,320 --> 01:16:59,090
Sir!

1169
01:17:02,360 --> 01:17:03,500
Every time I come,

1170
01:17:03,830 --> 01:17:05,940
it's always this man causing trouble.

1171
01:17:05,940 --> 01:17:06,710
Sir.

1172
01:17:07,540 --> 01:17:09,720
It was my ignorance that caused this mistake.

1173
01:17:09,720 --> 01:17:11,320
Please forgive me.

1174
01:17:11,500 --> 01:17:14,580
I heard strange rumors, so I came to check.

1175
01:17:15,730 --> 01:17:18,170
And indeed, your behavior is peculiar.

1176
01:17:19,700 --> 01:17:22,070
Yes, that's right, it's all my fault.

1177
01:17:22,440 --> 01:17:23,920
Punish me instead.

1178
01:17:24,040 --> 01:17:25,730
Please release my son.

1179
01:17:25,930 --> 01:17:30,180
Violating the strict laws of the state is punishable by death. No more words.

1180
01:17:30,500 --> 01:17:31,400
Yes, that's true.

1181
01:17:31,780 --> 01:17:33,890
What you say is reasonable.

1182
01:17:34,410 --> 01:17:34,860
But

1183
01:17:35,310 --> 01:17:36,590
one hundred strokes...

1184
01:17:37,100 --> 01:17:39,280
Even if he doesn't die, he'll be crippled!

1185
01:17:41,130 --> 01:17:41,900
Continue the beating.

1186
01:17:42,480 --> 01:17:43,150
Sir!

1187
01:17:43,150 --> 01:17:43,850
What are you waiting for?

1188
01:17:44,560 --> 01:17:45,390
Continue.

1189
01:17:45,650 --> 01:17:46,350
-Yes. -Sir.

1190
01:17:46,860 --> 01:17:48,590
Thirteen strokes.

1191
01:17:49,110 --> 01:17:49,940
Stop!

1192
01:18:11,630 --> 01:18:13,110
Release him at once.

1193
01:18:13,810 --> 01:18:16,180
He entered and left the exile grounds without permission.

1194
01:18:16,550 --> 01:18:17,570
Perhaps he was stealing,

1195
01:18:17,960 --> 01:18:20,850
or even plotting harm against Prince Nosan.

1196
01:18:20,850 --> 01:18:21,810
I called him here.

1197
01:18:22,830 --> 01:18:25,330
Life in exile is lonely. I wanted someone to talk to.

1198
01:18:26,050 --> 01:18:27,650
I called him, so

1199
01:18:28,590 --> 01:18:29,680
release him now.

1200
01:18:30,510 --> 01:18:32,310
What should we do, Inspector?

1201
01:18:40,500 --> 01:18:41,520
Continue the beating.

1202
01:18:42,510 --> 01:18:43,340
Sir.

1203
01:18:43,550 --> 01:18:44,780
Please, sir…

1204
01:18:44,780 --> 01:18:46,590
Beat him to death.

1205
01:18:46,590 --> 01:18:47,550
Sir!

1206
01:18:47,850 --> 01:18:48,610
Sir!

1207
01:18:49,020 --> 01:18:50,240
Beat him to death.

1208
01:18:50,380 --> 01:18:54,420
Han Myong-heo, how dare you insult the royal family!

1209
01:18:56,530 --> 01:18:58,000
Nosan.

1210
01:18:58,000 --> 01:19:00,720
He still thinks he's king.

1211
01:19:03,190 --> 01:19:05,240
Han Myong-heo, you wretch!

1212
01:19:06,710 --> 01:19:07,350
Beat him!

1213
01:19:08,570 --> 01:19:11,640
Beat him to death!

1214
01:19:12,280 --> 01:19:14,070
I said stop!

1215
01:19:14,070 --> 01:19:15,220
Prince Nosan,

1216
01:19:15,800 --> 01:19:18,180
if you do not return to the place of exile immediately,

1217
01:19:19,390 --> 01:19:21,700
he will be beaten two hundred, three hundred times.

1218
01:19:23,430 --> 01:19:26,250
That man will be beaten to death today.

1219
01:19:27,200 --> 01:19:28,100
Sir,

1220
01:19:28,350 --> 01:19:29,440
if you act like this,

1221
01:19:29,760 --> 01:19:31,600
we will suffer even more.

1222
01:19:31,600 --> 01:19:33,150
Please go back.

1223
01:19:34,220 --> 01:19:36,010
We can't let Tae-san be beaten to death.

1224
01:19:43,180 --> 01:19:45,100
Please… go back.

1225
01:19:50,860 --> 01:19:51,570
What are you waiting for?

1226
01:19:51,940 --> 01:19:54,130
Escort Prince Nosan back to the place of exile.

1227
01:20:02,130 --> 01:20:02,960
I'm a lowly wretch.

1228
01:20:03,790 --> 01:20:06,160
Forgetting my place and doing what I shouldn't.

1229
01:20:07,250 --> 01:20:11,980
I forgot whom I should follow and whose orders I should obey.

1230
01:20:12,500 --> 01:20:14,100
I forgot who the king of this country is now.

1231
01:20:34,380 --> 01:20:36,690
We cannot delay even a moment.

1232
01:20:37,650 --> 01:20:39,570
Nosan's eyes have changed.

1233
01:20:40,890 --> 01:20:43,090
Those weak, sickly eyes.

1234
01:20:44,240 --> 01:20:45,460
Here,

1235
01:20:47,180 --> 01:20:48,910
they've turned into blazing eyes.

1236
01:20:56,470 --> 01:20:57,790
The criminal, Prince Nosan.

1237
01:20:59,060 --> 01:21:03,220
That man still thinks he's king.

1238
01:21:04,230 --> 01:21:05,000
Beat him.

1239
01:21:05,700 --> 01:21:08,840
Beat him to death.

1240
01:21:11,210 --> 01:21:12,040
Your Highness.

1241
01:21:13,060 --> 01:21:17,110
We earnestly beg you to grant us your consent in a reply.

1242
01:21:23,410 --> 01:21:26,480
Grand Prince Geumseong is raising troops

1243
01:21:27,050 --> 01:21:28,430
to depose the current ruler

1244
01:21:28,430 --> 01:21:31,370
and restore Nosan to the throne. This is now clear.

1245
01:21:31,950 --> 01:21:36,230
Contact more local magistrates and officials willing to join.

1246
01:21:39,110 --> 01:21:40,270
Keep it as secret as possible.

1247
01:21:45,810 --> 01:21:48,950
After today, Nosan's resolve will only grow stronger.

1248
01:21:51,270 --> 01:21:55,300
He will surely join the rebellion.

1249
01:22:52,040 --> 01:22:53,510
Only if he dies

1250
01:22:54,020 --> 01:22:55,430
will your son live.

1251
01:22:56,070 --> 01:22:56,780
And

1252
01:22:57,160 --> 01:22:58,380
the village will survive.

1253
01:22:59,910 --> 01:23:05,290
You must obtain evidence of the rebellion.

1254
01:23:07,840 --> 01:23:10,720
All forces for the march on Hanyang are ready.

1255
01:23:11,040 --> 01:23:12,390
We can delay no longer.

1256
01:23:13,150 --> 01:23:16,420
Even without His Highness's consent, we must rise.

1257
01:23:19,050 --> 01:23:19,880
What is the situation?

1258
01:23:26,680 --> 01:23:27,380
Uncle.

1259
01:23:28,400 --> 01:23:31,480
I am no longer a weak exile,

1260
01:23:31,990 --> 01:23:33,330
but a witness to history,

1261
01:23:34,100 --> 01:23:35,960
who will stand shoulder to shoulder with you.

1262
01:23:37,750 --> 01:23:40,630
If a successful rebellion becomes the master of history,

1263
01:23:41,140 --> 01:23:45,500
then Joseon from this day forward will be a blood-soaked struggle for the throne, led by blades and spears,

1264
01:23:46,090 --> 01:23:49,330
lasting for decades, even centuries.

1265
01:23:50,610 --> 01:23:54,450
Even if the uprising fails,

1266
01:23:55,480 --> 01:23:57,650
we will fight to the death,

1267
01:23:58,680 --> 01:24:00,790
and the record of our attempt to correct history

1268
01:24:01,100 --> 01:24:02,930
will be passed down to future generations.

1269
01:24:04,520 --> 01:24:06,680
Uncle, please remain in Sunheung.

1270
01:24:07,060 --> 01:24:09,050
I will go there instead.

1271
01:24:09,800 --> 01:24:12,720
To the great tree at the shrine on Mt. Madae that you mentioned.

1272
01:24:14,400 --> 01:24:17,520
To correct history once more,

1273
01:24:17,920 --> 01:24:21,590
for the ancestral altars of Joseon and the peace of its people.

1274
01:24:22,320 --> 01:24:24,750
Nosan is secretly corresponding with Grand Prince Geumseong.

1275
01:24:24,790 --> 01:24:27,010
Something unusual is happening in Sunheung.

1276
01:24:28,330 --> 01:24:30,810
A storm of bloodshed is coming.

1277
01:24:35,370 --> 01:24:36,760
Prepare at once and set out.

1278
01:24:36,960 --> 01:24:37,660
Yes, sir.

1279
01:24:39,720 --> 01:24:41,680
Everything is ready now.

1280
01:24:42,570 --> 01:24:45,210
Go to Mt. Madae immediately

1281
01:24:46,050 --> 01:24:48,590
and escort His Highness here.

1282
01:24:48,590 --> 01:24:50,660
I, Jo Yu-rye, Vice Director of the State Council,

1283
01:24:51,220 --> 01:24:52,780
will faithfully carry out this order.

1284
01:24:53,220 --> 01:24:53,900
Move out.

1285
01:24:53,900 --> 01:24:54,830
-Yes, sir. -Yes, sir.

1286
01:24:58,070 --> 01:25:02,230
The time to set things right and end the false history is today.

1287
01:25:03,010 --> 01:25:03,960
Today,

1288
01:25:04,350 --> 01:25:06,190
we will cut off this treacherous age

1289
01:25:06,740 --> 01:25:10,870
and establish a new Joseon that cares for all its people.

1290
01:25:11,290 --> 01:25:12,670
I will remain here

1291
01:25:13,100 --> 01:25:15,750
and join His Highness upon his arrival.

1292
01:25:16,060 --> 01:25:18,520
All forces, led by the Geumhwa unit,

1293
01:25:19,800 --> 01:25:21,530
are ready to present proof.

1294
01:25:27,020 --> 01:25:28,880
Charge!

1295
01:25:56,460 --> 01:25:57,590
Absolutely not.

1296
01:25:59,840 --> 01:26:01,110
What do you mean by that?

1297
01:26:02,460 --> 01:26:05,500
Lord Han Myong-heo told me

1298
01:26:06,200 --> 01:26:08,190
that Grand Prince Geumseong is inciting you to rebellion,

1299
01:26:08,650 --> 01:26:11,770
so I was ordered to report your every move.

1300
01:26:11,770 --> 01:26:13,160
If I detect any suspicious signs,

1301
01:26:13,160 --> 01:26:15,180
I must report to the authorities.

1302
01:26:16,860 --> 01:26:17,720
So

1303
01:26:20,690 --> 01:26:23,600
have you noticed anything suspicious?

1304
01:26:23,600 --> 01:26:24,380
Yes.

1305
01:26:25,520 --> 01:26:27,030
I saw it with my own eyes.

1306
01:26:27,030 --> 01:26:29,040
Someone took away a letter written in your own hand.

1307
01:26:33,840 --> 01:26:35,370
Stop here.

1308
01:26:39,410 --> 01:26:41,120
And if I refuse?

1309
01:26:42,480 --> 01:26:43,530
If you insist on going ahead,

1310
01:26:45,510 --> 01:26:46,320
then I…

1311
01:26:48,730 --> 01:26:50,260
will report it to the authorities.

1312
01:27:01,170 --> 01:27:02,450
Do you know

1313
01:27:03,060 --> 01:27:06,140
what it feels like to live a life not your own?

1314
01:27:07,780 --> 01:27:10,450
By my father's decree, I was made Crown Prince

1315
01:27:11,110 --> 01:27:12,550
and ascended the throne,

1316
01:27:13,580 --> 01:27:15,860
yet I was driven out by my uncle's ambition

1317
01:27:16,720 --> 01:27:18,490
and reduced to this state.

1318
01:27:20,200 --> 01:27:21,140
But now,

1319
01:27:22,020 --> 01:27:24,000
I finally understand

1320
01:27:25,340 --> 01:27:28,640
why Heaven has kept me alive until this day and

1321
01:27:29,740 --> 01:27:31,910
why I must live on.

1322
01:27:33,550 --> 01:27:35,590
And the ones who awakened me to this truth

1323
01:27:35,940 --> 01:27:37,250
are you and Tae-san,

1324
01:27:38,550 --> 01:27:40,230
and the people of this village.

1325
01:27:42,400 --> 01:27:44,210
I will not stop.

1326
01:27:45,060 --> 01:27:46,440
As for you,

1327
01:27:47,920 --> 01:27:49,120
go to the authorities.

1328
01:27:50,620 --> 01:27:51,640
That way,

1329
01:27:52,330 --> 01:27:54,180
you and everyone in the village

1330
01:27:55,430 --> 01:27:57,420
can escape safely.

1331
01:28:40,110 --> 01:28:41,030
Sir.

1332
01:28:42,330 --> 01:28:43,220
Sir!

1333
01:28:50,810 --> 01:28:53,590
Are you really determined to go?

1334
01:28:56,520 --> 01:28:57,950
I don't want to lose

1335
01:28:59,400 --> 01:29:02,770
everyone I cherish because of myself ever again.

1336
01:29:04,560 --> 01:29:05,440
Please convey my regards

1337
01:29:06,680 --> 01:29:07,920
to everyone.

1338
01:29:13,590 --> 01:29:14,290
Does that

1339
01:29:16,960 --> 01:29:18,370
include me as well?

1340
01:29:21,100 --> 01:29:24,290
You said you don't want to lose those you cherish.

1341
01:29:26,790 --> 01:29:28,530
Am I one of them too?

1342
01:29:38,420 --> 01:29:40,780
Am I not, to you?

1343
01:29:44,610 --> 01:29:46,180
Of course you are.

1344
01:29:51,390 --> 01:29:53,460
How are our troops moving?

1345
01:29:55,100 --> 01:29:58,810
By now, our forces should have passed Danyang and reached Jecheon.

1346
01:29:58,940 --> 01:30:01,900
Another unit, scheduled to rendezvous, has already been waiting here.

1347
01:30:17,460 --> 01:30:18,730
All troops,

1348
01:30:19,510 --> 01:30:22,420
advance immediately!

1349
01:30:31,780 --> 01:30:34,790
Once the two forces join, our momentum and morale

1350
01:30:34,790 --> 01:30:36,350
will soar to the skies.

1351
01:30:36,350 --> 01:30:38,680
The combined army will advance along the route,

1352
01:30:38,680 --> 01:30:41,150
pass through Yeoju, and gather at Maebong Mountain,

1353
01:30:41,150 --> 01:30:44,380
awaiting orders from His Highness and the Grand Prince.

1354
01:30:44,380 --> 01:30:47,120
Once His Highness reaches the assembly point at Maebong Mountain,

1355
01:30:47,120 --> 01:30:50,160
we can reach Sungnyemun in Hanyang before dawn.

1356
01:30:50,160 --> 01:30:53,640
From Sungnyemun to the royal palace will take no more than half a quarter-hour.

1357
01:30:53,640 --> 01:30:56,550
The gate commander has already secretly allied with us,

1358
01:30:56,550 --> 01:30:58,500
and there are only two hundred enemy troops in the palace.

1359
01:30:58,500 --> 01:31:00,500
We have eighteen hundred soldiers.

1360
01:31:00,620 --> 01:31:02,610
Victory is only a matter of time.

1361
01:31:04,710 --> 01:31:06,830
By now, His Highness must have successfully made contact.

1362
01:31:08,250 --> 01:31:13,580
He must safely meet the Vice Director of the State Council.

1363
01:31:17,760 --> 01:31:19,210
Are you alright?

1364
01:31:19,210 --> 01:31:21,050
I'm fine.

1365
01:31:21,810 --> 01:31:25,400
I suddenly remembered when I first met you, sir,

1366
01:31:25,420 --> 01:31:26,490
at Cheongnyeongpo.

1367
01:31:28,080 --> 01:31:31,490
Is that so? What was I like back then?

1368
01:31:32,230 --> 01:31:33,680
What do you think you were like?

1369
01:31:36,620 --> 01:31:40,020
Truly elegant and strikingly handsome.

1370
01:31:42,020 --> 01:31:44,110
In terms of looks, I was clearly better.

1371
01:31:52,340 --> 01:31:53,360
Let's go.

1372
01:31:57,420 --> 01:31:58,640
We're almost there.

1373
01:32:00,050 --> 01:32:01,550
This is the City God Shrine.

1374
01:32:07,080 --> 01:32:07,830
Wait here for a moment.

1375
01:32:15,750 --> 01:32:17,080
There's no one around.

1376
01:32:17,500 --> 01:32:19,130
This should be the place.

1377
01:32:22,830 --> 01:32:23,610
Who's there?

1378
01:32:24,350 --> 01:32:25,130
Who is it?

1379
01:32:28,350 --> 01:32:29,180
Your Highness.

1380
01:32:29,790 --> 01:32:32,490
I am Jo Yu-rye, Vice Director of the State Council.

1381
01:32:35,590 --> 01:32:38,380
You've traveled a long way. Well done.

1382
01:32:38,380 --> 01:32:40,310
Everything is ready for the uprising.

1383
01:32:41,030 --> 01:32:42,270
Your Highness, please depart.

1384
01:32:45,440 --> 01:32:46,180
Let's go.

1385
01:32:49,130 --> 01:32:51,940
Why the rush?

1386
01:33:07,590 --> 01:33:08,910
Han Myong-heo.

1387
01:33:16,750 --> 01:33:23,700
Do you know why I exiled Geumseong and Nosan to such nearby places as Sujin and Yeongwol?

1388
01:33:24,730 --> 01:33:28,450
It was to wait for those with ill intent to collude and meet

1389
01:33:28,450 --> 01:33:30,140
and then

1390
01:33:31,700 --> 01:33:36,470
eliminate these vicious traitors all at once.

1391
01:33:45,410 --> 01:33:47,650
You all protect His Highness.

1392
01:33:47,820 --> 01:33:49,340
I'll hold them off here.

1393
01:33:49,340 --> 01:33:50,120
-Yes, sir. -Yes, sir.

1394
01:34:07,990 --> 01:34:10,790
They should have arrived by now. Why are they still not here?

1395
01:34:10,790 --> 01:34:12,780
We can't delay any longer.

1396
01:34:12,780 --> 01:34:15,240
The longer large-scale troop movements take,

1397
01:34:15,240 --> 01:34:16,910
the easier it is for the enemy to notice.

1398
01:34:16,920 --> 01:34:17,790
That's right.

1399
01:34:17,810 --> 01:34:20,530
We can't just sit here and wait, Your Highness.

1400
01:34:37,290 --> 01:34:39,290
Hold the line at all costs.

1401
01:35:13,820 --> 01:35:15,420
Pursue them with full force.

1402
01:35:24,210 --> 01:35:26,330
Head to Mt. Madae in Hanyang.

1403
01:35:26,330 --> 01:35:28,630
We'll personally escort His Highness there

1404
01:35:29,500 --> 01:35:31,820
and then advance on Hanyang.

1405
01:35:39,190 --> 01:35:40,730
Protect His Highness at all costs.

1406
01:35:45,630 --> 01:35:46,980
Sir!

1407
01:36:06,590 --> 01:36:08,760
The more you resist,

1408
01:36:09,620 --> 01:36:12,840
the more your followers will bleed and die in vain.

1409
01:36:13,920 --> 01:36:19,140
Han Myong-heo, do you truly wish to be remembered as a criminal in history?

1410
01:36:19,140 --> 01:36:20,860
I told you

1411
01:36:22,280 --> 01:36:25,890
I would come back to you with a sword in one hand and rewards in the other.

1412
01:36:26,180 --> 01:36:27,770
Yet you dared

1413
01:36:28,140 --> 01:36:31,300
to take up arms and betray your word.

1414
01:36:32,040 --> 01:36:34,370
You and your son, needless to say...

1415
01:36:35,230 --> 01:36:41,040
Your entire village will be wiped out.

1416
01:36:41,530 --> 01:36:44,700
Then you might as well kill me.

1417
01:36:44,700 --> 01:36:45,830
You traitor!

1418
01:36:49,530 --> 01:36:51,200
You read my secret letter,

1419
01:36:51,200 --> 01:36:53,050
pretended to guide us

1420
01:36:53,050 --> 01:36:54,830
so it was all a trap you had prepared.

1421
01:36:54,920 --> 01:36:58,330
You swore loyalty to Han Myong-heo.

1422
01:36:58,540 --> 01:37:00,290
What did he promise you?

1423
01:37:00,810 --> 01:37:03,110
Was it to make your son an official?

1424
01:37:03,490 --> 01:37:05,400
You shameless wretch!

1425
01:37:09,670 --> 01:37:11,000
Sir.

1426
01:37:12,860 --> 01:37:14,990
No need to say more.

1427
01:37:18,120 --> 01:37:20,180
At this point, it no longer matters.

1428
01:37:20,810 --> 01:37:23,010
Arrest the traitor.

1429
01:37:23,040 --> 01:37:23,870
-Yes, sir. -Yes, sir.

1430
01:37:25,820 --> 01:37:27,340
I…

1431
01:37:35,740 --> 01:37:37,160
Sir!

1432
01:37:37,380 --> 01:37:38,960
Sir!

1433
01:37:43,050 --> 01:37:47,060
Sir…

1434
01:37:49,800 --> 01:37:52,160
The traitor Geumseong,

1435
01:37:53,130 --> 01:37:54,280
is to be given poison.

1436
01:38:12,270 --> 01:38:13,100
Your Highness.

1437
01:38:13,950 --> 01:38:15,550
it is I, Geumseong.

1438
01:38:16,850 --> 01:38:18,050
I am incompetent

1439
01:38:18,870 --> 01:38:22,120
and failed to protect you.

1440
01:38:23,600 --> 01:38:24,500
Please

1441
01:38:27,470 --> 01:38:28,900
take care of yourself.

1442
01:39:00,350 --> 01:39:01,270
Sir.

1443
01:39:03,670 --> 01:39:05,120
Why did you do this?

1444
01:39:08,070 --> 01:39:10,120
Why bear everything alone?

1445
01:39:46,770 --> 01:39:47,870
Come in.

1446
01:39:56,470 --> 01:39:57,250
This way, please.

1447
01:40:31,550 --> 01:40:33,150
Have you been well?

1448
01:40:34,200 --> 01:40:38,550
I often think of the jelly soup Mo-tong made.

1449
01:40:39,500 --> 01:40:42,520
I wonder if Mo-tong has finished memorizing the Thousand Character Classic.

1450
01:40:43,370 --> 01:40:47,670
I also worry about Tae-san, who was beaten.

1451
01:40:48,620 --> 01:40:49,950
Have his wounds healed?

1452
01:40:51,670 --> 01:40:54,870
Everyone is well.

1453
01:40:55,250 --> 01:40:56,320
And

1454
01:40:57,420 --> 01:41:00,650
more than anything, they miss the face of their guardian.

1455
01:41:02,150 --> 01:41:04,970
Are you referring to my handsome face?

1456
01:41:05,550 --> 01:41:06,970
Look again closely.

1457
01:41:08,950 --> 01:41:10,920
It truly is quite remarkable.

1458
01:41:41,470 --> 01:41:45,270
I have something important to entrust to you.

1459
01:41:46,420 --> 01:41:47,270
Yes.

1460
01:41:48,220 --> 01:41:49,420
Please give your orders.

1461
01:41:56,270 --> 01:42:00,770
The traitor Yi Hong-wi is to be given poison.

1462
01:42:03,450 --> 01:42:05,000
The rebel Yi Hong-wi,

1463
01:42:05,800 --> 01:42:09,470
despite receiving the boundless grace of His Majesty,

1464
01:42:10,070 --> 01:42:15,000
conspired with Grand Prince Geumseong in a treason punishable by heaven and man.

1465
01:42:15,420 --> 01:42:17,850
Therefore, poison is bestowed upon him.

1466
01:42:19,570 --> 01:42:22,750
This is a royal decree, come out and receive it.

1467
01:42:25,500 --> 01:42:27,970
No… that's not true.

1468
01:42:36,970 --> 01:42:38,300
Drag the criminal out.

1469
01:42:39,170 --> 01:42:40,000
-Yes. -Yes.

1470
01:42:53,370 --> 01:42:54,470
Insolence!

1471
01:42:55,570 --> 01:42:58,450
How dare you invade a royal residence!

1472
01:43:01,100 --> 01:43:04,500
Am I, an old man,

1473
01:43:05,300 --> 01:43:09,720
unable to deal with a single traitor? What nonsense is this!

1474
01:43:11,770 --> 01:43:13,320
Give me a moment.

1475
01:43:14,800 --> 01:43:17,970
I will drag that traitor out.

1476
01:43:26,650 --> 01:43:27,500
No…

1477
01:43:44,270 --> 01:43:45,520
Your Highness.

1478
01:43:48,070 --> 01:43:49,900
I am Eom Heung-do, your guardian.

1479
01:43:52,070 --> 01:43:52,820
Now,

1480
01:43:54,320 --> 01:43:56,170
it is time to cross the river.

1481
01:44:03,000 --> 01:44:04,300
When the moment comes,

1482
01:44:05,250 --> 01:44:06,600
use that bowstring.

1483
01:44:07,620 --> 01:44:08,370
You must

1484
01:44:09,850 --> 01:44:12,800
kill me with your own hands.

1485
01:44:18,300 --> 01:44:20,200
I do not wish to die at their hands,

1486
01:44:21,900 --> 01:44:25,720
nor by the poison they grant.

1487
01:44:27,870 --> 01:44:29,100
Even in death, I would not accept that.

1488
01:44:35,220 --> 01:44:36,270
I beg you,

1489
01:44:37,900 --> 01:44:39,300
with your own hands,

1490
01:44:41,900 --> 01:44:43,450
send me across the river.

1491
01:44:59,250 --> 01:45:00,320
Your Highness.

1492
01:45:03,500 --> 01:45:04,270
Alright.

1493
01:45:06,950 --> 01:45:09,150
I will send you across.

1494
01:45:17,670 --> 01:45:19,150
Let's go.

1495
01:45:33,100 --> 01:45:33,970
Alright.

1496
01:45:57,350 --> 01:45:58,400
Let's go.

1497
01:46:00,050 --> 01:46:00,870
Alright.

1498
01:46:05,900 --> 01:46:07,170
Your Highness.

1499
01:46:07,870 --> 01:46:09,400
It is time to depart.

1500
01:46:11,600 --> 01:46:14,320
It is time to depart.

1501
01:46:29,770 --> 01:46:33,420
It is time to depart.

1502
01:46:43,920 --> 01:46:46,770
Please endure a little longer.

1503
01:46:47,120 --> 01:46:48,620
We're almost there.

1504
01:46:49,120 --> 01:46:51,570
We're almost there, Your Highness.

1505
01:46:52,420 --> 01:46:57,300
We've reached the riverbank.

1506
01:47:02,920 --> 01:47:06,600
It is time to depart.

1507
01:47:22,600 --> 01:47:23,820
Your Highness.

1508
01:47:32,520 --> 01:47:34,670
Your Highness.

1509
01:48:38,420 --> 01:48:42,450
Anyone who collects or buries Nosan's body

1510
01:48:42,450 --> 01:48:46,220
will have their entire family exterminated.

1511
01:48:51,650 --> 01:48:54,100
From the time I first learned to walk,

1512
01:48:54,770 --> 01:48:56,450
you were always by my side.

1513
01:48:57,920 --> 01:49:02,620
To me, you were a dear friend, an elder sister, and like a mother.

1514
01:49:04,220 --> 01:49:06,320
Leaving behind these cherished years,

1515
01:49:07,270 --> 01:49:08,920
I will depart.

1516
01:49:10,600 --> 01:49:13,720
If we meet again in a distant next life,

1517
01:49:14,950 --> 01:49:18,970
I hope we can once again be close friends.

1518
01:49:20,500 --> 01:49:24,750
And when that time comes, I will gladly stay by your side.

1519
01:50:06,770 --> 01:50:07,850
Sir.

1520
01:50:38,150 --> 01:50:39,300
It's cold, isn't it?

1521
01:50:52,120 --> 01:50:54,470
Let's go. Let's get out of here.

1522
01:50:55,820 --> 01:50:59,270
Let's go somewhere warm.

1523
01:51:00,950 --> 01:51:02,200
Let's go.

1524
01:51:04,220 --> 01:51:05,400
Let's go.

1525
01:51:07,620 --> 01:51:19,160
A court attendant
who had long served Prince Nosan volunteered for the task.
He tied a long rope to the bowstring
and pulled it tight through the gap behind the seat.
That year, Yi Hong-wi was only seventeen.
— Records of the Yeollyeosil, Annals of King Danjong

1526
01:51:19,760 --> 01:51:31,010
When Prince Nosan was killed, no one dared tend to his body.
A local official, Eom Heung-do, went to mourn him,
personally prepared a coffin, and buried him.
The present-day royal tomb stands on that very site.
— Annals of King Hyeonjong, Year 10, January 5

1527
01:51:31,940 --> 01:51:41,120
Despite many trying to stop him, Eom Heung-do said:
“To uphold righteousness and suffer misfortune is something I willingly accept, not something I fear.”
— Biographical Records of the Joseon Dynasty

1528
01:51:42,020 --> 01:51:51,560
Two hundred forty-one years later,
Yi Hong-wi was restored as King Danjong,
and Eom Heung-do, recognized for his loyalty, was posthumously honored as Lord Chungui.

1529
01:51:55,130 --> 01:52:03,110
Today, their graves stand together in Yeongwol.

1530
01:52:04,570 --> 01:52:10,780
The King's Warden

1531
01:52:13,220 --> 01:52:16,020
Yoo Hae-jin

1532
01:52:16,720 --> 01:52:19,520
Park Ji-hoon

1533
01:52:20,220 --> 01:52:23,090
Yoo Ji-tae

1534
01:52:23,690 --> 01:52:26,560
Jeon Mi-do

1535
01:52:27,200 --> 01:52:30,070
Directed by Jang Hang-jun
